1
00:01:10,505 --> 00:01:13,546
Do they lay you face up or face down
in your grave?

2
00:01:13,630 --> 00:01:15,588
We cremate our dead, so I'm not sure.

3
00:01:43,296 --> 00:01:45,130
[reporter 1] Mr Amre,
what would you like to say?

4
00:01:45,213 --> 00:01:48,088
I am here to give these people
one last and final warning.

5
00:01:49,130 --> 00:01:52,296
Under the guise of massage parlours,
they're running sleazy businesses

6
00:01:52,380 --> 00:01:55,380
and attempting to defame
India's great culture and value system.

7
00:01:56,421 --> 00:01:58,921
And I swear by the thousands of workers
standing with me,

8
00:01:59,005 --> 00:02:01,171
if I win the upcoming elections…

9
00:02:01,255 --> 00:02:03,713
I will shut down
this entire illegal racket.

10
00:02:04,296 --> 00:02:05,630
And for our country's women,

11
00:02:05,713 --> 00:02:07,713
who work in these suspicious
massage parlours,

12
00:02:08,338 --> 00:02:11,380
I shall do everything I can to find them
honest employment

13
00:02:11,463 --> 00:02:13,130
and help them get back
on their feet again.

14
00:02:13,213 --> 00:02:14,296
That is all I have to say.

15
00:02:14,380 --> 00:02:16,421
- What kind of leader do we want?
- [reporter 2] One more question, sir!

16
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:21,380
[laughs]

17
00:02:23,713 --> 00:02:24,838
[laughs]

18
00:02:24,921 --> 00:02:26,171
Hey!

19
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:29,963
Not here.

20
00:02:30,671 --> 00:02:31,755
Only inside.

21
00:02:32,588 --> 00:02:34,088
- Okay!
- Go!

22
00:02:36,005 --> 00:02:37,213
Go!

23
00:03:09,255 --> 00:03:10,296
[moaning]

24
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:12,421
[Amre] Say my name, Amre.

25
00:03:13,963 --> 00:03:15,546
- Amru, Amru.
- [moaning]

26
00:03:19,088 --> 00:03:22,588
Respected sir, I have recorded
everything you did in your room today.

27
00:03:22,671 --> 00:03:24,630
Sending you a teaser. Also note, sir,

28
00:03:24,713 --> 00:03:28,463
if anything happens to me, even a
viral flu, your video will go viral too.

29
00:03:31,338 --> 00:03:34,630
[man] Listen, I'm sorry, madam.
I don't think you understand.

30
00:03:34,713 --> 00:03:38,213
In the last two days,
I've called you six times already.

31
00:03:38,296 --> 00:03:39,713
[operator] I understand, sir.

32
00:03:39,796 --> 00:03:41,755
May I please put you
on hold for two minutes?

33
00:03:41,838 --> 00:03:44,463
No, no, no. Please don't put me on hold.

34
00:03:44,546 --> 00:03:46,505
As it is, the music you play is terrible.

35
00:03:47,046 --> 00:03:48,255
You're not getting it.

36
00:03:49,296 --> 00:03:51,130
- Six rupees.
- Good morning, sir.

37
00:03:51,213 --> 00:03:54,421
You know, in last month's phone bill,
my wife had to pay six rupees extra.

38
00:03:54,505 --> 00:03:57,296
[operator] Yes, sir. It will
be credited to your account next month.

39
00:03:57,380 --> 00:03:59,671
- But why are you panting, sir?
- Why am I panting?

40
00:04:00,713 --> 00:04:02,296
[panting]

41
00:04:02,380 --> 00:04:04,005
- What's your name, again?
- It's Payal.

42
00:04:05,255 --> 00:04:08,630
So this call I made, is it being recorded
for quality purposes?

43
00:04:09,213 --> 00:04:10,588
Yes, sir.

44
00:04:10,671 --> 00:04:12,088
Very good.

45
00:04:12,171 --> 00:04:16,963
So, Payal, my dear,
I am a 73-year-old man. Okay?

46
00:04:17,046 --> 00:04:18,130
[panting]

47
00:04:18,213 --> 00:04:20,171
This stress you're putting me through…

48
00:04:20,255 --> 00:04:24,463
At this rate, your current customer
will become my future widow very soon.

49
00:04:25,213 --> 00:04:26,546
Sir, please don't stress.

50
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:29,463
Your charges will definitely be reversed
in your next month's bill.

51
00:04:29,546 --> 00:04:33,380
Next month? Next month,
my wife will have to take you to court.

52
00:04:34,005 --> 00:04:35,421
For my… For my heart attack.

53
00:04:35,505 --> 00:04:36,921
[coughs]

54
00:04:38,588 --> 00:04:40,755
Payal, listen. Do me a favour.

55
00:04:40,838 --> 00:04:45,213
See, you can refund it to me in cash.
I'll come to your headquarters. Okay?

56
00:04:45,296 --> 00:04:47,380
[operator]
Sorry, sir. I can only credit it.

57
00:04:47,463 --> 00:04:50,213
But thank you for calling Telecorex.
An executive…

58
00:04:56,546 --> 00:04:57,755
Good morning, uncle.

59
00:04:58,505 --> 00:04:59,921
[panting]

60
00:05:00,005 --> 00:05:01,088
Hey!

61
00:05:03,130 --> 00:05:04,130
What?

62
00:05:04,213 --> 00:05:06,005
- How much?
- 307.

63
00:05:06,088 --> 00:05:07,171
Five hundred.

64
00:05:08,296 --> 00:05:11,796
I wasn't out shopping all morning.
I have been working out.

65
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,088
Oh, yeah?

66
00:05:13,171 --> 00:05:15,338
- Did you steal this from the temple?
- Hey!

67
00:05:15,963 --> 00:05:17,046
- Hey!
- Huh?

68
00:05:17,130 --> 00:05:20,921
Hey. [stammers] My banana!

69
00:05:21,671 --> 00:05:23,088
My banana.

70
00:05:23,171 --> 00:05:24,421
- He will pay.
- [grunts]

71
00:05:24,505 --> 00:05:25,838
Cut it from the rent.

72
00:05:27,421 --> 00:05:28,588
Take a shower for God's sake.

73
00:05:29,505 --> 00:05:30,713
- How much is it?
- Three hundred and seven.

74
00:05:30,796 --> 00:05:31,796
Three hundred and…

75
00:05:34,296 --> 00:05:36,213
Where the hell is he coming from?

76
00:05:39,213 --> 00:05:42,255
Our country's by-lanes may be narrow,

77
00:05:42,338 --> 00:05:44,963
but the stories they tell
are very intriguing.

78
00:05:45,755 --> 00:05:48,380
Today's incident is no different.

79
00:05:48,463 --> 00:05:52,088
It makes you sit up and wonder,
what caused this death?

80
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:55,755
Was it the awful recipe for the okra curry

81
00:05:55,838 --> 00:05:59,630
that Pappu's mother criticised
in the common group chat?

82
00:05:59,713 --> 00:06:02,046
- There's plenty of natural light.
- [reporter] Or was it Mrs Srivastav?

83
00:06:02,130 --> 00:06:05,296
Why do you need the light on?
Just switch it off.

84
00:06:05,921 --> 00:06:08,296
Mumbai winter doesn't last
for more than a few days.

85
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:10,005
Enjoy. Why do you need the fan?

86
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:12,213
They say it might even snow this time.

87
00:06:12,296 --> 00:06:13,338
- Really?
- Hmm.

88
00:06:13,421 --> 00:06:16,713
Global warming, bro, global warming.
Good, we'll save on expenses.

89
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,921
Shilpa, why do you have to watch
these gory murder mysteries

90
00:06:20,005 --> 00:06:21,005
first thing in the morning?

91
00:06:21,088 --> 00:06:23,338
One day, we too might end up like this.

92
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,880
End up like this?

93
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:27,463
If someone does…

94
00:06:27,546 --> 00:06:28,838
[gasps]

95
00:06:28,921 --> 00:06:30,005
…I'll flip them over.

96
00:06:30,088 --> 00:06:32,588
I don't have a black belt in judo
just to hold my pants up.

97
00:06:32,671 --> 00:06:34,588
- I'll save you.
- [chuckles]

98
00:06:34,671 --> 00:06:36,588
And who will save you from me?

99
00:06:36,671 --> 00:06:38,880
[both chuckle]

100
00:06:38,963 --> 00:06:41,671
What are you staring at?
These two gray hairs of mine?

101
00:06:41,755 --> 00:06:43,421
No, no! You're looking hot.

102
00:06:43,505 --> 00:06:45,380
You can go butter your old aunties, okay?

103
00:06:45,963 --> 00:06:48,130
I'll turn into an old hag
if we continue to live here.

104
00:06:48,213 --> 00:06:50,463
I'll dye your grey hair with watercolours.

105
00:06:50,546 --> 00:06:51,963
Watercolour will not disguise
my grey hair.

106
00:06:52,546 --> 00:06:54,880
This apartment complex
shouldn't be called "Peace Apartments,"

107
00:06:54,963 --> 00:06:56,088
but "Rest in Peace Apartments."

108
00:06:56,171 --> 00:06:57,171
[chuckles]

109
00:06:57,255 --> 00:06:58,755
Why can't we move somewhere else?

110
00:06:59,755 --> 00:07:02,296
Shilpa! Don't start again!

111
00:07:03,005 --> 00:07:05,713
The rent here is so low,
it's still stuck in the dark ages.

112
00:07:07,171 --> 00:07:08,171
This…

113
00:07:08,963 --> 00:07:11,505
Mrs Fateha's head scarf. It falls here
every day. And you know what?

114
00:07:11,588 --> 00:07:13,755
You won't find a cheaper, prettier
place anywhere else.

115
00:07:13,838 --> 00:07:15,505
Honey, I'm serious.

116
00:07:15,588 --> 00:07:17,463
I can't handle these old fogeys anymore.

117
00:07:17,546 --> 00:07:18,713
Come on, let's make a baby.

118
00:07:18,796 --> 00:07:21,880
Hey! One second, one second!
What's wrong with you?

119
00:07:21,963 --> 00:07:24,171
You're bored, so you have a baby?
Is that how it works?

120
00:07:24,255 --> 00:07:27,088
Look, if you're bored, watch TV.
Scroll reels.

121
00:07:27,838 --> 00:07:30,630
Shilpa, kids are a lifetime investment
with zero returns. No benefits at all.

122
00:07:30,713 --> 00:07:31,921
Get lost.

123
00:07:32,005 --> 00:07:33,005
Uh…

124
00:07:34,338 --> 00:07:36,421
Okay, listen. There's some good news.

125
00:07:36,505 --> 00:07:37,838
What is it?

126
00:07:37,921 --> 00:07:40,171
I just spoke with the Telecorex people.

127
00:07:40,255 --> 00:07:42,046
- Hmm?
- Remember the six bucks?

128
00:07:42,130 --> 00:07:43,963
They'll credit it
to your next month's bill.

129
00:07:44,046 --> 00:07:45,255
Enjoy!

130
00:07:46,421 --> 00:07:47,505
Six bucks.

131
00:07:48,130 --> 00:07:50,046
All this effort for six bloody bucks?

132
00:07:50,796 --> 00:07:52,505
Your obsession with money
is getting worse.

133
00:07:52,588 --> 00:07:55,130
It's six whole bucks.
That's hard-earned money.

134
00:07:55,213 --> 00:07:57,546
You can get two bananas for six bucks
if you bargain really hard.

135
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,713
Just forget it.

136
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,421
Would you like some hard-earned
porridge or bread?

137
00:08:01,505 --> 00:08:03,171
Neither.

138
00:08:03,255 --> 00:08:06,713
Free toast. At Mrs D'Souza's place.

139
00:08:06,796 --> 00:08:09,088
By the way,
there's also free dinner today.

140
00:08:09,588 --> 00:08:11,213
- Free dinner? How come?
- Yeah.

141
00:08:12,005 --> 00:08:13,296
You've forgotten?

142
00:08:13,380 --> 00:08:14,880
It's my Guruji's daughter's wedding.

143
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,880
Once again?

144
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:19,463
How many daughters does your Guruji have?

145
00:08:20,213 --> 00:08:22,963
Come home early this evening.
We have to pick up a gift.

146
00:08:23,046 --> 00:08:24,213
A gift?

147
00:08:35,755 --> 00:08:36,838
[Shilpa's spouse] Mrs D'Souza.

148
00:08:37,921 --> 00:08:39,338
Mrs…

149
00:08:39,421 --> 00:08:40,963
Good morning!

150
00:08:41,046 --> 00:08:42,671
Good morning, Ramakant.

151
00:08:42,755 --> 00:08:44,755
- Good morning.
- Hmm, how are you?

152
00:08:44,838 --> 00:08:46,963
- I'm good. Thank you.
- Mmm.

153
00:08:47,046 --> 00:08:49,713
And here you go.
Medication for your constipation.

154
00:08:49,796 --> 00:08:53,296
Ooh! You're such an angel.
Thank you for remembering.

155
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:55,963
Oh, no Mrs D'Souza.
If I don't take care of you, who will?

156
00:08:56,046 --> 00:08:57,755
- [Ramakant chuckles] You see…
- Mmm.

157
00:08:57,838 --> 00:08:59,963
…I missed my breakfast since
I was running around for your medicine.

158
00:09:00,046 --> 00:09:01,546
Oh! Breakfast?

159
00:09:02,171 --> 00:09:03,171
Yeah, sure.

160
00:09:06,171 --> 00:09:07,296
Toast? Ah.

161
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,380
Mmm.

162
00:09:09,796 --> 00:09:10,963
Oh, no, no, no! It's burnt.

163
00:09:11,046 --> 00:09:12,963
- No, no. It's okay. It's okay.
- Okay.

164
00:09:13,046 --> 00:09:15,130
This damn toaster's not working properly.

165
00:09:18,046 --> 00:09:20,755
What happened? Did you poop this morning?

166
00:09:20,838 --> 00:09:22,546
I did, a bit.

167
00:09:23,380 --> 00:09:24,463
So, Mrs D'Souza.

168
00:09:24,546 --> 00:09:26,921
Did I tell you Shilpa's
going ahead with the IVF?

169
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,046
- We're trying for a baby, you know.
- Mm-hmm.

170
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:31,505
It took a lot of convincing.

171
00:09:32,671 --> 00:09:33,963
But I love kids.

172
00:09:35,088 --> 00:09:37,921
It's very expensive.
Our expenses are through the roof.

173
00:09:40,088 --> 00:09:41,505
Mrs D'Souza,

174
00:09:42,505 --> 00:09:45,713
if the rent could be reduced a little,
it would be of great help.

175
00:09:46,546 --> 00:09:48,630
- Uh.
- Why don't you let me butter your bread?

176
00:09:49,213 --> 00:09:52,630
Mmm. Go slow on the buttering.
There will be no discount on the rent.

177
00:09:52,713 --> 00:09:53,796
Bloody con man.

178
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,255
Bloody chimney!

179
00:09:55,338 --> 00:09:58,463
It's my house! And only I decide
what happens here and what doesn't!

180
00:09:58,546 --> 00:10:00,088
Go back to your beach house. Go!

181
00:10:00,755 --> 00:10:02,838
- Five hundred less.
- [playful music plays]

182
00:10:06,546 --> 00:10:07,546
Go, go.

183
00:10:11,296 --> 00:10:14,713
Can you reduce it
a little more than five hundred?

184
00:10:14,796 --> 00:10:16,380
[visitor] D'Souza.

185
00:10:16,463 --> 00:10:18,755
Your favourite marmalade… oh.

186
00:10:18,838 --> 00:10:21,505
- Marmalade I've got for you.
- Aw! Thank you so much!

187
00:10:21,588 --> 00:10:22,588
- [chuckles]
- Eat it.

188
00:10:22,671 --> 00:10:24,088
- Hello, Mrs Pherwani.
- Hello.

189
00:10:24,171 --> 00:10:25,796
Come. Please sit, please come sit.
I was just leaving.

190
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:27,880
[Pherwani] Thank you. Thank you.

191
00:10:27,963 --> 00:10:29,255
[groans]

192
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,213
Noir Mirage?

193
00:10:32,296 --> 00:10:35,963
- Oh! Yes.
- [chuckles] Suits your personality.

194
00:10:36,046 --> 00:10:37,088
Thank you.

195
00:10:37,171 --> 00:10:38,755
It's on discount at my store.

196
00:10:38,838 --> 00:10:41,171
Very good.

197
00:10:41,255 --> 00:10:42,796
- Okay, Mrs D'Souza.
- Okay.

198
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,963
- We'll talk later. Do let me know.
- Yeah. Bye.

199
00:10:45,046 --> 00:10:46,505
- Bye, Mrs Pherwani.
- Bye.

200
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:53,130
Guddu, what is this? Such a huge amount.

201
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:56,505
Did you bring back a camel from Dubai
this time along with the perfume?

202
00:10:56,588 --> 00:10:59,380
You're selling fake stuff
at genuine prices.

203
00:10:59,463 --> 00:11:01,963
But don't wanna pay the genuine price
to me for the fake stuff?

204
00:11:02,046 --> 00:11:03,838
- No, no…
- Take it back. He doesn't want it.

205
00:11:03,921 --> 00:11:05,880
No, no. Don't do that. Listen.

206
00:11:05,963 --> 00:11:07,046
Bring it here.

207
00:11:07,130 --> 00:11:09,296
Come on, Guddu. Why would you do that?

208
00:11:09,380 --> 00:11:11,005
You're my bro.

209
00:11:11,088 --> 00:11:14,921
This is great. You put a gun to my head
and conduct business.

210
00:11:15,755 --> 00:11:17,046
My father was a shooter.

211
00:11:18,130 --> 00:11:19,213
It's just that…

212
00:11:20,005 --> 00:11:22,213
I had to get into this business
for my mother's sake.

213
00:11:23,255 --> 00:11:24,380
[sighs]

214
00:11:24,463 --> 00:11:26,963
Guddu, please see what you can do.
A small discount.

215
00:11:27,046 --> 00:11:28,463
Ramakant.

216
00:11:28,546 --> 00:11:29,796
Special tea? With milk?

217
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,880
No!

218
00:11:31,713 --> 00:11:33,005
I'm lactose intolerant.

219
00:11:33,755 --> 00:11:36,380
- What?
- Lactose intolerant.

220
00:11:37,671 --> 00:11:39,505
- I see.
- You know what that is, right?

221
00:11:39,588 --> 00:11:40,838
[sighs]

222
00:11:40,921 --> 00:11:42,796
Listen, forget about it.
Just pay for this.

223
00:11:53,463 --> 00:11:55,005
I told you to come home early today.

224
00:11:55,630 --> 00:11:57,130
Put on your jacket.
We're getting late for the wedding.

225
00:11:57,213 --> 00:11:59,713
Yeah. I was packing a gift for the couple.

226
00:12:00,755 --> 00:12:02,296
What's that huge thing you've bought?

227
00:12:02,380 --> 00:12:04,630
It's your Guruji's daughter's wedding.
It has to be big.

228
00:12:08,838 --> 00:12:10,755
Hey! What are you doing?

229
00:12:11,505 --> 00:12:13,130
[stammers] Why are you tearing…

230
00:12:24,088 --> 00:12:25,338
You like it?

231
00:12:25,421 --> 00:12:26,546
This is a tester, right?

232
00:12:27,213 --> 00:12:28,630
Is the label still on?

233
00:12:28,713 --> 00:12:29,713
No.

234
00:12:30,588 --> 00:12:32,046
Then how did you know?

235
00:12:32,130 --> 00:12:34,005
Because I know you.

236
00:12:35,046 --> 00:12:37,213
Yeah, but it seems like your Guruji's
daughter's wedding

237
00:12:37,296 --> 00:12:39,005
is like some festival
that happens every year.

238
00:12:39,088 --> 00:12:43,130
You can say what you like. I'm going to
get them a gift that's nice and expensive.

239
00:12:43,213 --> 00:12:44,546
Shut the shop and let's go.

240
00:12:44,630 --> 00:12:47,380
But, Shilpa, it's a nice gift.
It's a new tester.

241
00:12:48,255 --> 00:12:49,255
Hey…

242
00:12:52,921 --> 00:12:54,296
Let's get them an extension cord?

243
00:12:54,380 --> 00:12:56,463
You can buy an extension cord
for your house.

244
00:12:56,546 --> 00:12:57,630
- Hello, sir. Hello, ma'am.
- Hello.

245
00:12:58,505 --> 00:12:59,838
- Hmm.
- [Ramakant groans]

246
00:12:59,921 --> 00:13:01,005
Take a look at this.

247
00:13:01,088 --> 00:13:04,796
This is our new range
of appliances for the new-age family.

248
00:13:04,880 --> 00:13:07,171
Anything for five or six hundred?

249
00:13:07,255 --> 00:13:10,671
Sir, data cable and mouse
is available in 550 rupees.

250
00:13:10,755 --> 00:13:12,005
Sounds good. Let's take it.

251
00:13:12,755 --> 00:13:15,713
Ma'am, you tell me what you like
from all these. What about this one?

252
00:13:16,588 --> 00:13:18,380
And this. This one.

253
00:13:18,463 --> 00:13:19,588
I like this. How much is it?

254
00:13:19,671 --> 00:13:21,463
Five-and-a-half thousand only.

255
00:13:21,546 --> 00:13:22,963
Five-and-a-half thousand?

256
00:13:23,046 --> 00:13:24,671
Yes, sir. That's what I just said.

257
00:13:24,755 --> 00:13:26,421
Is it made of silver or something?

258
00:13:26,505 --> 00:13:28,255
Sir, stainless steel.

259
00:13:28,338 --> 00:13:30,338
These days, even marriages
don't last a lifetime,

260
00:13:30,421 --> 00:13:32,713
but this toaster comes
with a lifetime warranty, sir.

261
00:13:32,796 --> 00:13:35,546
So relationships stay warm and crispy
for a lifetime.

262
00:13:36,130 --> 00:13:38,505
Twelve hundred is a good price.
It's so light anyway.

263
00:13:38,588 --> 00:13:40,421
Sir, this is a showroom.

264
00:13:40,505 --> 00:13:41,838
Not a flea market.

265
00:13:41,921 --> 00:13:44,255
He's fleecing us.
What he's quoting is very high.

266
00:13:44,338 --> 00:13:46,880
I'm not listening
to any of your nonsense today.

267
00:13:46,963 --> 00:13:49,630
Only for you, ma'am,
five thousand a piece only.

268
00:13:49,713 --> 00:13:52,130
- [chuckles]
- Special discount for a special lady.

269
00:13:53,338 --> 00:13:54,546
What's so special about her?

270
00:13:56,921 --> 00:13:58,880
Fine, special price for the both of us.
Fifteen hundred.

271
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:00,171
You may pack it, please.

272
00:14:00,255 --> 00:14:02,338
Great choice, ma'am. Great choice.

273
00:14:02,421 --> 00:14:03,463
He said 5,000!

274
00:14:04,088 --> 00:14:06,713
We can get it for 12 hundred… Shilpa!

275
00:14:21,838 --> 00:14:23,296
What on earth are you doing?

276
00:14:24,255 --> 00:14:26,963
Two vehicles will burn double the fuel,
pollution will increase.

277
00:14:27,046 --> 00:14:28,213
We need to be responsible.

278
00:14:29,046 --> 00:14:30,338
I know exactly what you're doing.

279
00:14:30,421 --> 00:14:33,338
Stop trying to be another
Greta Thunberg. Let go of that.

280
00:14:33,421 --> 00:14:34,671
Who?

281
00:14:34,755 --> 00:14:35,921
Shut up and let go of it.

282
00:14:37,838 --> 00:14:38,921
[clicks tongue]

283
00:14:39,005 --> 00:14:40,796
[people cheering]

284
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,838
It's a new toaster. Worth 6,000.

285
00:14:42,921 --> 00:14:44,046
Thank you.

286
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:48,880
We plan to get this one married next year.

287
00:14:48,963 --> 00:14:50,046
- Yes. Yes, sir.
- [Guruji chuckles]

288
00:14:50,130 --> 00:14:51,463
But she's already married to you, right?

289
00:14:51,546 --> 00:14:53,296
No, no. He means our daughter.

290
00:14:53,380 --> 00:14:54,421
[Guruji laughs]

291
00:14:54,505 --> 00:14:56,380
- [photographer] One picture, sir.
- Sure.

292
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,171
Um…

293
00:14:59,255 --> 00:15:00,588
Hold this a little higher.

294
00:15:02,005 --> 00:15:04,588
[people chattering]

295
00:15:07,255 --> 00:15:09,505
Are you trying to recover your five grand
through the food?

296
00:15:12,213 --> 00:15:13,671
Do you see that?

297
00:15:13,755 --> 00:15:16,546
Our toaster is shining on that table.

298
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:17,671
The biggest one.

299
00:15:18,463 --> 00:15:20,796
Tell your Guruji,
he shouldn't just get you a job,

300
00:15:20,880 --> 00:15:22,380
he should even get you
an Olympic medal too.

301
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,255
Make sure you don't miss the ice cream.

302
00:15:25,171 --> 00:15:26,838
We'll eat here,

303
00:15:26,921 --> 00:15:28,088
- and pack a doggy-bag too.
- Ramakant!

304
00:15:28,171 --> 00:15:29,588
- What?
- What are you doing?

305
00:15:30,796 --> 00:15:32,921
They just dump it. They waste food.

306
00:15:33,796 --> 00:15:35,005
We'll make use of it.

307
00:15:36,630 --> 00:15:38,255
- How is it?
- Hmm.

308
00:15:41,921 --> 00:15:43,046
It's good. Mmm.

309
00:15:44,838 --> 00:15:47,546
Put some more.
We gifted them a toaster worth 7,000.

310
00:15:47,630 --> 00:15:48,755
[guests cheering]

311
00:15:48,838 --> 00:15:51,213
Oh, yeah. Get some chocolate syrup too,
your favourite.

312
00:15:51,296 --> 00:15:52,296
Yeah, yeah. Lots of it.

313
00:15:52,380 --> 00:15:54,005
Raj, let's…

314
00:15:54,088 --> 00:15:55,838
Oh! Sorry.

315
00:15:56,421 --> 00:15:58,463
- I think I mistook you for my husband.
- [chuckles]

316
00:15:58,546 --> 00:16:00,796
He's also wearing a jacket
of the same colour.

317
00:16:02,171 --> 00:16:05,463
- Sorry. Sorry.
- It's okay. [chuckles]

318
00:16:06,755 --> 00:16:08,671
Oof! She's so hot!

319
00:16:09,213 --> 00:16:10,421
Check her out.

320
00:16:12,130 --> 00:16:15,130
If you take your eyes off your own wife,
you're done for life.

321
00:16:16,963 --> 00:16:20,046
And anyway, the only woman
I find special is you.

322
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:31,546
What? I saw a case exactly like this
on that crime show the other day.

323
00:16:32,088 --> 00:16:33,255
Hmm.

324
00:16:34,796 --> 00:16:35,921
Yeah.

325
00:16:37,880 --> 00:16:39,005
How is Guruji?

326
00:16:41,380 --> 00:16:42,588
Yeah.

327
00:16:43,588 --> 00:16:45,088
Okay. Yeah, bye.

328
00:16:45,171 --> 00:16:46,630
- [clicks tongue]
- What happened?

329
00:16:46,713 --> 00:16:50,046
The groom's girlfriend showed up
in the middle of the ceremony.

330
00:16:50,130 --> 00:16:53,171
He's been sleeping with her
this entire time. She was pregnant.

331
00:16:53,255 --> 00:16:54,421
- What?
- Hmm.

332
00:16:55,296 --> 00:16:57,088
So, what happens to…

333
00:16:57,171 --> 00:16:59,588
The wedding is off.
What'll happen to the poor bride now?

334
00:16:59,671 --> 00:17:01,088
Oh, to hell with her!

335
00:17:01,755 --> 00:17:02,963
What happens with the toaster?

336
00:17:04,005 --> 00:17:05,088
What?

337
00:17:05,171 --> 00:17:07,630
Hey, we gifted them a toaster
worth 5,000 yesterday.

338
00:17:07,713 --> 00:17:08,880
What happens to that?

339
00:17:08,963 --> 00:17:10,588
To hell with your bloody toaster!

340
00:17:10,671 --> 00:17:13,171
A girl's life has been ruined, and
you're rambling on about your toaster.

341
00:17:13,255 --> 00:17:18,421
[stammers] No, no. I mean, her life is not
ruined. In fact, she's been saved.

342
00:17:18,505 --> 00:17:19,796
Oh, shut up!

343
00:17:19,880 --> 00:17:22,963
Listen, love.
Let's go to Guruji's place this evening.

344
00:17:23,796 --> 00:17:24,921
Um…

345
00:17:25,630 --> 00:17:27,713
[stammers] What I feel is, right now,

346
00:17:27,796 --> 00:17:29,505
- the wound is still fresh.
- Hmm.

347
00:17:29,588 --> 00:17:32,463
We should give them some space.
At least for now. Huh?

348
00:17:32,546 --> 00:17:33,921
We'll go some other time.

349
00:17:38,671 --> 00:17:41,838
[clicks tongue] Pregnant girlfriend?

350
00:17:41,921 --> 00:17:43,796
- [crying]
- [glass shattering]

351
00:17:43,880 --> 00:17:45,838
Shilpa said we should go some other time.
I said, "No!"

352
00:17:45,921 --> 00:17:47,921
"He's my Guruji. I'll go right away."

353
00:17:49,005 --> 00:17:51,630
Look, it's okay to share happiness
with any and everyone.

354
00:17:51,713 --> 00:17:53,046
But when it comes to sorrow…

355
00:17:54,505 --> 00:17:55,880
you need your own people.

356
00:17:58,796 --> 00:18:00,005
[sighs]

357
00:18:00,713 --> 00:18:01,880
Sorry?

358
00:18:01,963 --> 00:18:04,505
Sure, I'll have tea. With some snacks.

359
00:18:06,546 --> 00:18:08,088
[sighs]

360
00:18:08,171 --> 00:18:10,046
Now don't rush
with the younger one's marriage.

361
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:12,338
Wait for four or five years, okay?

362
00:18:12,421 --> 00:18:13,588
You're quite right, son.

363
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:16,921
And now you've been saddled
with another task.

364
00:18:17,005 --> 00:18:19,213
You received so many gifts at the wedding.

365
00:18:19,296 --> 00:18:22,171
You'll have to find out who gave what,
and then return them.

366
00:18:22,921 --> 00:18:26,255
- But the wedding gift's for…
- No, no, no! I… I understand.

367
00:18:27,005 --> 00:18:30,046
I'll save you all the trouble,
and tell you what gift I gave.

368
00:18:31,088 --> 00:18:35,213
So, my gift was a toaster. The best gift
on the list. Worth 8,000.

369
00:18:36,171 --> 00:18:37,296
[dramatic playful music plays]

370
00:18:37,380 --> 00:18:41,671
I thought Soni could make her husband
some crispy toast every morning.

371
00:18:41,755 --> 00:18:43,005
[Guruji's wife sighs]

372
00:18:43,713 --> 00:18:46,171
[stutters] Could you send for the toaster?

373
00:18:46,255 --> 00:18:48,421
Son, we've donated all the wedding gifts.

374
00:18:50,171 --> 00:18:51,505
Donated them?

375
00:18:51,588 --> 00:18:53,963
We gave them all to an orphanage.

376
00:18:54,713 --> 00:18:56,546
How could you just donate them like that?

377
00:18:56,630 --> 00:18:57,713
Why?

378
00:18:57,796 --> 00:18:59,338
Those were our gifts.

379
00:18:59,421 --> 00:19:01,838
So we donated them.
Why are you so bothered?

380
00:19:01,921 --> 00:19:03,546
Your gifts?

381
00:19:03,630 --> 00:19:05,755
The wedding didn't happen.
How can they be your gifts?

382
00:19:05,838 --> 00:19:08,380
Wedding cancelled, gifts cancelled.
I'd like my toaster back.

383
00:19:08,463 --> 00:19:11,255
[stammers] No, what I'm saying is…

384
00:19:11,338 --> 00:19:13,505
Tomorrow, if Soni gets married again,
will we have to give another gift?

385
00:19:13,588 --> 00:19:14,671
Do we keep doing this?

386
00:19:14,755 --> 00:19:16,880
What makes you think
you'll be invited the next time?

387
00:19:17,421 --> 00:19:19,171
Get out! Get out!

388
00:19:19,255 --> 00:19:22,213
One second. One… one second.
One second. One second. One second.

389
00:19:23,838 --> 00:19:25,838
The snacks are coming.
Let's eat and then talk.

390
00:19:25,921 --> 00:19:28,130
- Get out of my house!
- Hey! Hey, my bag! My bag!

391
00:19:28,213 --> 00:19:30,713
[grunting] Hey, yellow belt!
My wife is a black belt.

392
00:19:30,796 --> 00:19:32,088
- She'll slam you down!
- Get out!

393
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:35,255
- Hey! But I want my toaster back!
- [cries]

394
00:19:38,255 --> 00:19:40,046
What's the name of the orphanage, you say?

395
00:19:41,671 --> 00:19:42,963
BAL BHAVAN ORPHANAGE

396
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:51,671
Hey, Pichkoo! You keep
putting your sticker all over the place.

397
00:19:51,755 --> 00:19:52,838
Who the hell do you think you are?

398
00:19:52,921 --> 00:19:54,755
Hey, excuse me. One minute.
Who's in charge around here?

399
00:19:54,838 --> 00:19:57,588
Ms Nandini. She's inside.
Hey, Pichkoo, stop!

400
00:20:00,171 --> 00:20:02,588
Chunnu, Munnu, make sure
you don't drop the lemon.

401
00:20:02,671 --> 00:20:05,296
Or you'll both have to keep at it
for one more hour.

402
00:20:06,380 --> 00:20:07,463
Um, ma'am.

403
00:20:07,546 --> 00:20:09,380
Just a minute. Please hold on.

404
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:18,171
Hmm. What do you want? A kid?

405
00:20:18,796 --> 00:20:21,046
We don't allow single men to adopt.
Too many issues.

406
00:20:21,130 --> 00:20:24,546
- No, no. Not a kid. I want this.
- Mmm. What?

407
00:20:24,630 --> 00:20:26,963
Toast?
Do you think I'm running a tea stall here?

408
00:20:27,046 --> 00:20:28,755
Hey, not the toast. I mean…

409
00:20:28,838 --> 00:20:31,796
the thing that you made the toast in.
The toaster. It's mine.

410
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:33,630
Hey? How could it be yours?

411
00:20:33,713 --> 00:20:37,671
That very nice judo-karate coach, he
donated it to us for the hungry orphans.

412
00:20:38,463 --> 00:20:40,755
- What? Judo-karate coach?
- Hmm.

413
00:20:40,838 --> 00:20:42,963
So now he's become a philanthropist?

414
00:20:43,046 --> 00:20:44,880
I gifted it to his daughter
at her wedding.

415
00:20:44,963 --> 00:20:46,380
- Oh, really?
- It's mine. Can I please have it back?

416
00:20:46,463 --> 00:20:48,546
Why should I believe you?
Do you have the receipt?

417
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:50,838
Who gives a receipt along with
a wedding gift?

418
00:20:50,921 --> 00:20:52,380
You think I'm some kind of cheapo?

419
00:20:52,463 --> 00:20:55,338
Who asks for a wedding gift to be
returned? Only a cheapo, right?

420
00:20:55,421 --> 00:20:57,005
Listen, I don't need
a character certificate from you.

421
00:20:57,088 --> 00:20:59,630
Mmm. If you had a character,
I might have given you a certificate.

422
00:21:00,713 --> 00:21:02,005
This is getting a bit much now!

423
00:21:02,088 --> 00:21:04,338
Listen, you. One second.
Here, here. I have this. Take a look.

424
00:21:04,421 --> 00:21:06,880
- What are you showing me?
- This is the warranty card. Heatpot.

425
00:21:08,380 --> 00:21:09,880
- Lifetime warranty?
- Yes.

426
00:21:09,963 --> 00:21:11,546
Oh, wow! Thank you.

427
00:21:11,630 --> 00:21:12,880
Hey!

428
00:21:12,963 --> 00:21:16,255
What a thief you are, lady. You kept it?

429
00:21:16,338 --> 00:21:19,255
What was that? Thief?

430
00:21:19,338 --> 00:21:20,671
How dare you say that?

431
00:21:21,630 --> 00:21:23,463
Hmm? I'm not a thief!

432
00:21:23,546 --> 00:21:25,880
I was sent to jail on false charges.

433
00:21:25,963 --> 00:21:28,588
- You are a thief! Your father's a thief!
- Hey. Your father…

434
00:21:28,671 --> 00:21:31,046
Don't drag my father into this!
Don't you dare abuse my father.

435
00:21:31,130 --> 00:21:33,588
He's also in jail on false charges.
Get out!

436
00:21:33,671 --> 00:21:35,088
Chunnu, Munnu, throw this man out.

437
00:21:35,171 --> 00:21:36,255
- Come on!
- Get out! Throw him out!

438
00:21:36,338 --> 00:21:37,796
- Throw this man out!
- Hey! Hey!

439
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,796
- He thinks he can come intimidate me?
- My toaster!

440
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:41,338
[Nandini] And take my toaster away?

441
00:21:47,421 --> 00:21:49,880
HOW MUCH MONEY DO YOU WANT?

442
00:21:49,963 --> 00:21:51,380
2 MILLION

443
00:21:53,505 --> 00:21:55,213
MY MAN WILL MEET YOU

444
00:22:05,171 --> 00:22:06,255
Hello?

445
00:22:06,338 --> 00:22:08,463
Yes, I bought a toaster
from you yesterday.

446
00:22:08,546 --> 00:22:11,671
I wanted to return it and get a refund.
But I don't have the receipt.

447
00:22:11,755 --> 00:22:14,380
Uh, sir, I'll have to speak
to my manager with regard to this.

448
00:22:14,463 --> 00:22:16,921
Yes, then connect me to him.
I'll talk to him myself.

449
00:22:17,005 --> 00:22:19,421
Sir, why are you getting worried?
I'll arrange for a call back with him.

450
00:22:19,505 --> 00:22:20,505
When will that be?

451
00:22:20,588 --> 00:22:22,963
Uh, the call can come at anytime, sir.
Just answer it.

452
00:22:23,046 --> 00:22:25,255
Yeah, sure, I'll be available.
You make sure you arrange it.

453
00:22:25,338 --> 00:22:26,838
Okay, sir.

454
00:22:27,588 --> 00:22:29,880
[Nandini] Mangesh.
Make sure you lock the gate.

455
00:22:29,963 --> 00:22:32,171
We don't want any kids
trying to run away again.

456
00:22:32,671 --> 00:22:34,255
I'll give you 30 bucks. Not a penny more.

457
00:22:35,671 --> 00:22:36,713
Now get lost.

458
00:22:37,963 --> 00:22:40,421
[Nandini] Now what?
Do I have to push the car?

459
00:22:42,255 --> 00:22:43,505
Start moving. Hurry up.

460
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:49,255
[Mangesh] You kids.
Can't find a better time to go for a pee?

461
00:23:51,380 --> 00:23:54,296
Move! Hurry up!

462
00:24:29,963 --> 00:24:32,421
[phone rings]

463
00:24:35,880 --> 00:24:36,963
What?

464
00:24:37,046 --> 00:24:38,630
What the hell did you do
at Guruji's place?

465
00:24:38,713 --> 00:24:39,921
Listen, I'll come home and explain.

466
00:24:40,005 --> 00:24:43,213
There's nothing to explain.
How could you do something like this?

467
00:24:43,296 --> 00:24:44,671
Don't you have any shame?

468
00:24:44,755 --> 00:24:46,713
Do you plan to snatch food
from hungry children next?

469
00:24:46,796 --> 00:24:48,755
- Snatched already.
- What?

470
00:24:48,838 --> 00:24:50,296
- [child 1] There's a thief.
- [Mangesh] Thief!

471
00:24:50,380 --> 00:24:53,171
[stutters] Some thief just snatched
a lady's handbag from her,

472
00:24:53,255 --> 00:24:55,171
I'll catch him and get back to you.
Okay, okay.

473
00:24:55,255 --> 00:24:57,130
[Mangesh] Thief! Thief! Thief! Catch him!

474
00:24:57,213 --> 00:24:59,755
[Mangesh] He's there! Thief! Thief! Thief!

475
00:24:59,838 --> 00:25:03,380
[child 2] Thief! Thief! Thief! Thief!
Catch him! Thief! Thief!

476
00:25:19,255 --> 00:25:21,713
[D'Souza] This bloody chimney!

477
00:25:21,796 --> 00:25:25,505
He wants me to dry his undies,
fry his eggs.

478
00:25:25,588 --> 00:25:28,546
And in return, he fries my brain.

479
00:25:28,630 --> 00:25:31,255
Damn useless, good for anything.

480
00:25:32,421 --> 00:25:33,505
[groans]

481
00:25:34,255 --> 00:25:36,463
Oh, God! Oh, God!

482
00:25:36,546 --> 00:25:37,963
- [humming]
- [playful music plays]

483
00:25:44,838 --> 00:25:46,588
[phone ringing]

484
00:25:57,213 --> 00:25:58,338
- Hello?
- [man] Good morning, sir.

485
00:25:58,421 --> 00:26:00,171
Our bank is happy to off you a loan of--

486
00:26:00,255 --> 00:26:02,296
Listen, I don't want a loan.
Please stop calling me.

487
00:26:05,671 --> 00:26:06,671
Ramakant?

488
00:26:09,130 --> 00:26:10,130
Present, ma'am.

489
00:26:17,921 --> 00:26:20,213
Have you heard of Bal Bhavan Orphanage?

490
00:26:20,296 --> 00:26:24,088
- Yes. You just mentioned it.
- Hey! Do you know of it or not?

491
00:26:24,838 --> 00:26:28,005
Bal Bhav… yes,
it sound vaguely familiar, ma'am.

492
00:26:28,088 --> 00:26:29,630
You went there last evening, didn't you?

493
00:26:29,713 --> 00:26:33,005
No, no, ma'am. We were both here,
at home, playing board games.

494
00:26:33,713 --> 00:26:38,130
Last night, someone stole
a brand-new toaster from their place.

495
00:26:38,213 --> 00:26:41,130
Now, since we received a complaint,
we have to investigate.

496
00:26:41,213 --> 00:26:42,338
So, what are you trying to say?

497
00:26:42,421 --> 00:26:44,838
That you were the one
who stole that toaster.

498
00:26:44,921 --> 00:26:47,046
Ma'am, how can you fling
such a crude allegation at me?

499
00:26:47,130 --> 00:26:51,171
And not just that! You also stole
two packets of the kids' biscuits.

500
00:26:51,255 --> 00:26:53,421
That lady who runs the orphanage, Nandini,

501
00:26:53,505 --> 00:26:56,338
she said you went there
to demand she return the toaster to you.

502
00:26:56,421 --> 00:26:58,463
When she refused, you grabbed it and left.

503
00:26:58,546 --> 00:27:00,338
Ma'am, I'm telling you
she's poisoned your ears against me.

504
00:27:00,421 --> 00:27:02,546
Back off.
And sit down with your legs crossed.

505
00:27:02,630 --> 00:27:04,630
Or I'll break them.

506
00:27:04,713 --> 00:27:07,005
What? My legs? Okay.

507
00:27:07,088 --> 00:27:09,380
Okay, now spill.

508
00:27:09,463 --> 00:27:12,463
[stammers]
One second. What… Bal… Bal Bhav…

509
00:27:12,546 --> 00:27:17,213
Oh, yes, ma'am, yes. Now I remember.
Yeah! I remembered, I remember!

510
00:27:17,296 --> 00:27:20,171
Why didn't you say so earlier? I…
[chuckles]

511
00:27:20,255 --> 00:27:22,338
Shilpa, I did go there yesterday.

512
00:27:22,421 --> 00:27:24,755
To give the warranty card, ma'am,
for the toaster.

513
00:27:26,088 --> 00:27:27,588
What's written on my forehead?

514
00:27:29,463 --> 00:27:31,546
Hey! Tell the truth!

515
00:27:33,380 --> 00:27:34,880
All right, ma'am.

516
00:27:34,963 --> 00:27:36,088
I'll tell you the truth.

517
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:39,255
I did go to the orphanage.

518
00:27:40,296 --> 00:27:42,255
And the lady in charge, Ms Nandini,

519
00:27:42,338 --> 00:27:45,213
she feeds nothing but dry bread
to the poor orphans.

520
00:27:45,296 --> 00:27:47,338
You hold it like this,
it crumbles into powder.

521
00:27:47,421 --> 00:27:51,005
But she herself smears her toast
with butter and stuffs her face with it.

522
00:27:51,088 --> 00:27:53,171
I told her I would expose her.

523
00:27:53,255 --> 00:27:55,546
That's why… that's why she got upset.

524
00:27:56,505 --> 00:27:57,671
As for the biscuits?

525
00:27:57,755 --> 00:28:00,630
Ma'am, I'm the kind of person
who will go without food,

526
00:28:00,713 --> 00:28:03,171
but will stand at the traffic lights
to distribute biscuits to poor kids.

527
00:28:03,255 --> 00:28:05,130
And their mothers as well.

528
00:28:05,880 --> 00:28:07,880
You can ask my wife about it.
She'll tell you.

529
00:28:07,963 --> 00:28:11,463
Um, tell them, Shilpa. Tell her the truth.

530
00:28:13,630 --> 00:28:14,671
The truth?

531
00:28:17,130 --> 00:28:18,755
- You think he's a suspect?
- Yes.

532
00:28:19,505 --> 00:28:21,130
Then go ahead and search.

533
00:28:21,213 --> 00:28:22,421
Yes, ma'am. Please search me.

534
00:28:22,505 --> 00:28:23,796
The house.

535
00:28:24,380 --> 00:28:25,671
Start searching, you guys.

536
00:28:34,046 --> 00:28:36,546
We also misplaced our nail-cutter.
See if you can find it.

537
00:28:36,630 --> 00:28:38,088
Make hay while the sun shines.

538
00:28:38,171 --> 00:28:40,088
[playful music plays]

539
00:28:57,171 --> 00:28:58,463
Anything?

540
00:28:58,546 --> 00:29:01,130
- Couldn't find it, madam.
- [constable] Nothing here, madam.

541
00:29:03,546 --> 00:29:05,796
I'm sure he's hidden it somewhere.

542
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:07,796
- I'll give him two slaps if…
- No!

543
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:11,005
You know that women constables
are forbidden from touching men.

544
00:29:13,713 --> 00:29:14,796
Okay.

545
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:18,213
[groans]

546
00:29:18,296 --> 00:29:19,296
Was that okay for you?

547
00:29:20,088 --> 00:29:22,130
When the police chief lands up here,

548
00:29:22,213 --> 00:29:24,421
he'll strip him naked
and drag him to the station.

549
00:29:24,505 --> 00:29:26,588
Yeah. You didn't find the toaster, right?

550
00:29:26,671 --> 00:29:28,671
Next time, make sure
you carry a search warrant.

551
00:29:28,755 --> 00:29:30,505
For now, get out.

552
00:29:30,588 --> 00:29:32,130
- Out!
- Let's go, let's go!

553
00:29:32,213 --> 00:29:33,255
Out!

554
00:29:33,338 --> 00:29:34,755
Get out!

555
00:29:34,838 --> 00:29:36,463
Out!

556
00:29:38,088 --> 00:29:39,671
[door closes]

557
00:29:42,463 --> 00:29:43,755
Did he hurt you?

558
00:29:44,921 --> 00:29:46,046
Huh!

559
00:29:56,005 --> 00:29:57,171
Morning, Mama.

560
00:29:57,796 --> 00:30:00,546
Oh! Holy mother of God!

561
00:30:00,630 --> 00:30:04,838
How come this bat woke up so early
in the morning, like a normal human being?

562
00:30:04,921 --> 00:30:06,421
I've got work, Mama.

563
00:30:07,046 --> 00:30:08,880
Oh. Work! [chuckles]

564
00:30:08,963 --> 00:30:12,213
The stash is finished.
Need to go score some more.

565
00:30:12,296 --> 00:30:14,130
It's a genuine job, Mama.

566
00:30:14,213 --> 00:30:18,796
Oh! Genuine! Okay, okay. Genuine job.

567
00:30:19,588 --> 00:30:23,755
Do one genuine job for me too.
Get my toaster fixed.

568
00:30:23,838 --> 00:30:25,921
And mind you, if you sell it,

569
00:30:26,005 --> 00:30:29,130
I promise I'll sell
you straight to India's Most Wanted.

570
00:30:38,046 --> 00:30:41,671
Rascal! He didn't even take my toaster.

571
00:30:44,171 --> 00:30:45,380
Lunch.

572
00:30:45,463 --> 00:30:47,546
I didn't go to your Guruji's
to take anything.

573
00:30:47,630 --> 00:30:49,463
But to give him the warranty card.

574
00:30:49,546 --> 00:30:51,171
And they misunderstood me.

575
00:30:51,255 --> 00:30:54,005
Today that lady cop called me a thief
in my own home.

576
00:30:55,921 --> 00:30:58,838
The world can call me whatever.
It makes no difference to me.

577
00:31:00,088 --> 00:31:01,213
But you…

578
00:31:06,296 --> 00:31:07,921
I've lost my appetite.

579
00:31:11,296 --> 00:31:12,296
[person] Hey.

580
00:31:13,463 --> 00:31:15,546
- Some juice.
- But you already have some.

581
00:31:15,630 --> 00:31:17,380
- [person 2] Take your food and move ahead.
- Okay.

582
00:31:17,463 --> 00:31:21,088
This has been generously organised
by Mr Amre. Please move ahead.

583
00:31:21,171 --> 00:31:22,171
Come on.

584
00:31:22,255 --> 00:31:23,380
Now I don't.

585
00:31:23,463 --> 00:31:24,546
Take this.

586
00:31:40,213 --> 00:31:41,963
Huh?

587
00:31:42,046 --> 00:31:43,713
Hey, hey! Finish it, finish it.

588
00:31:57,921 --> 00:31:59,588
Excuse me. Excuse me. Excuse me.

589
00:32:24,921 --> 00:32:29,421
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah! Yes!

590
00:32:30,046 --> 00:32:32,421
You better move it,
darling, or you'll die.

591
00:32:34,046 --> 00:32:37,130
Wow! What an awesome sticker, that is.

592
00:32:37,213 --> 00:32:38,963
Pichkoo!

593
00:32:39,046 --> 00:32:41,046
Okay, forget that. Let's play.

594
00:32:41,130 --> 00:32:42,838
[video game music plays]

595
00:32:45,421 --> 00:32:46,838
What about the deal, dude?

596
00:32:47,671 --> 00:32:49,130
Yeah.

597
00:32:49,213 --> 00:32:50,963
Ever since we got your message,

598
00:32:51,046 --> 00:32:53,005
Mr Amre has stopped thinking
about the country,

599
00:32:53,088 --> 00:32:55,130
or the city and its problems entirely.

600
00:32:56,338 --> 00:32:58,046
He's been thinking only about you.

601
00:33:00,588 --> 00:33:01,755
Let's go, darling.

602
00:33:02,755 --> 00:33:04,338
Think and name your price.

603
00:33:06,130 --> 00:33:07,130
It's fixed.

604
00:33:07,213 --> 00:33:10,046
Just remember, it's an Amru Amre matter.

605
00:33:11,755 --> 00:33:14,213
[laughs]

606
00:33:14,296 --> 00:33:16,588
I come to this place every Sunday.

607
00:33:16,671 --> 00:33:17,755
It's fun.

608
00:33:17,838 --> 00:33:19,255
[laughs]

609
00:33:25,671 --> 00:33:28,046
- [screaming]
- [screaming]

610
00:33:41,963 --> 00:33:44,838
[laughing, panting]

611
00:33:54,338 --> 00:33:56,880
[crowd screaming, shouting]

612
00:33:56,963 --> 00:33:58,171
So, darling?

613
00:34:00,713 --> 00:34:02,088
Did you have fun?

614
00:34:02,838 --> 00:34:04,130
Because of?

615
00:34:04,838 --> 00:34:05,963
Safety belts, yeah.

616
00:34:07,088 --> 00:34:09,505
But safety belts in life don't exist.

617
00:34:10,296 --> 00:34:11,421
Anything can happen.

618
00:34:12,213 --> 00:34:15,171
Road accident, drug overdose.

619
00:34:15,963 --> 00:34:17,630
Or they murder you.

620
00:34:17,713 --> 00:34:20,171
But show it as suicide. Who knows?

621
00:34:21,630 --> 00:34:23,755
You just never know. Anything can happen.

622
00:34:25,921 --> 00:34:27,130
Okay, then.

623
00:34:27,213 --> 00:34:29,838
I'll come soon
to pick up my stuff from you.

624
00:34:31,088 --> 00:34:34,005
And to enjoy butter and toast
made by your mom.

625
00:34:34,588 --> 00:34:35,588
Yeah?

626
00:34:35,671 --> 00:34:37,880
All right. Take care.

627
00:34:37,963 --> 00:34:38,963
Bye.

628
00:35:11,421 --> 00:35:12,630
[pants]

629
00:35:13,505 --> 00:35:16,255
Mama. Mama, you okay?

630
00:35:16,338 --> 00:35:17,838
[groans] Yeah.

631
00:35:17,921 --> 00:35:20,296
Uh, yeah. [groans]

632
00:35:20,380 --> 00:35:24,505
Ever since you popped out,
nothing else ever did.

633
00:35:24,588 --> 00:35:26,005
- [huffing]
- Don't worry, Ma.

634
00:35:26,088 --> 00:35:28,255
- I am going to do something now…
- [grunting]

635
00:35:29,213 --> 00:35:31,046
…and pop right out of your life
in a flash.

636
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:32,546
Pop out!

637
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:34,255
Oh, please pop out!

638
00:35:34,338 --> 00:35:38,255
[groaning]
At least death will be peaceful.

639
00:35:39,463 --> 00:35:45,338
You didn't let me live in peace.
At least let me die!

640
00:35:56,588 --> 00:36:01,255
Hmm. It's the constipation
that brought on the heart attack.

641
00:36:01,338 --> 00:36:04,296
When you consume too much bread,
your stomach tends to bloat.

642
00:36:04,380 --> 00:36:06,963
It causes constipation.
I'm a doctor. I know about these things.

643
00:36:07,046 --> 00:36:08,046
Go slow.

644
00:36:08,130 --> 00:36:10,296
You're not at a party.
You're at a funeral.

645
00:36:10,380 --> 00:36:11,838
My father used to say,

646
00:36:12,546 --> 00:36:14,171
"The more you eat at a funeral,

647
00:36:14,255 --> 00:36:16,380
the more you feed the souls of those
who have passed."

648
00:36:16,463 --> 00:36:17,463
Huh.

649
00:36:17,546 --> 00:36:20,421
If you eat so much bread,
Aunty's soul will also get constipated.

650
00:36:20,505 --> 00:36:22,463
Have you tried my berry pulao?

651
00:36:22,546 --> 00:36:23,671
Hmm.

652
00:36:25,296 --> 00:36:26,421
Thank you, Aunty.

653
00:36:30,880 --> 00:36:32,088
He's going to sing.

654
00:36:32,796 --> 00:36:33,880
I…

655
00:36:34,838 --> 00:36:37,463
I would like to say two words
about my Mama.

656
00:36:41,005 --> 00:36:42,088
Mama.

657
00:36:45,088 --> 00:36:46,171
Mama.

658
00:36:50,005 --> 00:36:52,130
[crying]

659
00:36:54,630 --> 00:36:57,171
- Glen. My son.
- [cries]

660
00:36:57,255 --> 00:36:58,380
True to his word.

661
00:36:59,213 --> 00:37:00,671
Exactly two words.

662
00:37:04,171 --> 00:37:05,171
Excuse me.

663
00:37:05,255 --> 00:37:06,255
What is this?

664
00:37:09,921 --> 00:37:11,255
- [Glen crying]
- [smacks lips]

665
00:37:13,296 --> 00:37:14,505
I too

666
00:37:16,005 --> 00:37:18,838
would like to say something
about dear Mrs D'Souza.

667
00:37:19,713 --> 00:37:21,505
But a little more than two words.

668
00:37:23,838 --> 00:37:25,338
Mrs D'Souza…

669
00:37:25,421 --> 00:37:26,921
Best person.

670
00:37:27,005 --> 00:37:28,630
She used to treat me like her own son.

671
00:37:28,713 --> 00:37:30,005
Hey!

672
00:37:31,630 --> 00:37:33,130
In fact, even more than her own son.

673
00:37:33,213 --> 00:37:35,213
- [cries]
- No, no.

674
00:37:35,296 --> 00:37:37,921
Even as she was dying,
she continued to do good.

675
00:37:38,671 --> 00:37:40,505
Before she died, she even called me.

676
00:37:40,588 --> 00:37:42,171
She said,

677
00:37:43,546 --> 00:37:45,088
"Ramakant, my son.

678
00:37:46,505 --> 00:37:47,880
From today, your rent…

679
00:37:51,505 --> 00:37:52,630
is reduced by 5,000."

680
00:37:52,713 --> 00:37:54,588
- No!
- Yes!

681
00:37:54,671 --> 00:37:55,838
Maybe, maybe.

682
00:37:55,921 --> 00:37:57,255
[phone rings]

683
00:37:57,338 --> 00:37:58,838
I said, "Mrs D'Souza…"

684
00:37:58,921 --> 00:38:00,713
[ringing continues]

685
00:38:00,796 --> 00:38:02,046
One, one second.

686
00:38:02,671 --> 00:38:05,630
- I'm okay. I'm okay.
- Hello?

687
00:38:05,713 --> 00:38:07,796
Sir, can you bring over the toaster
in a day or two?

688
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,588
- I can arrange for the refund.
- It can be done?

689
00:38:09,671 --> 00:38:11,463
- Yes.
- I'll be there tomorrow morning.

690
00:38:11,546 --> 00:38:12,796
- Okay, sir.
- Yes, thank you.

691
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,630
Thank you, thank you.
Thank you. Thank you.

692
00:38:17,630 --> 00:38:20,213
Hey! What? Why?

693
00:38:22,296 --> 00:38:23,588
Thank you.

694
00:38:28,255 --> 00:38:29,713
- Mrs Pherwani.
- Mmm?

695
00:38:29,796 --> 00:38:32,505
Is there some leftover rice?
We can pack a doggy bag.

696
00:38:32,588 --> 00:38:35,546
- Of course. I'll get it…
- No. It's okay. I'll take it. Thank you.

697
00:38:48,130 --> 00:38:49,505
Hey!

698
00:38:49,588 --> 00:38:50,671
What are you doing?

699
00:38:51,296 --> 00:38:54,130
This is mine. I gave it to Mrs D'Souza
for safekeeping.

700
00:38:54,213 --> 00:38:55,338
You bloody vulture!

701
00:38:55,421 --> 00:38:57,338
Mama isn't even buried yet, and you?

702
00:38:57,421 --> 00:38:58,963
You're already here to steal her stuff?

703
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:01,671
You scavenger hyena!

704
00:39:01,755 --> 00:39:04,213
How dare… How dare you call me a vulture?

705
00:39:04,296 --> 00:39:05,796
This toaster is Mama's. Put it down!

706
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:08,255
- I bought it. It's my toaster.
- Put it down!

707
00:39:08,338 --> 00:39:10,463
This… This was Shilpa's surprise gift.

708
00:39:10,546 --> 00:39:12,296
And what's it to you? Huh?

709
00:39:12,380 --> 00:39:14,005
Now that Mrs D'Souza is gone.

710
00:39:14,088 --> 00:39:16,213
Sell everything in the house
and smoke it up? Buy drugs?

711
00:39:16,296 --> 00:39:18,171
Have some shame, you con artist!

712
00:39:18,255 --> 00:39:20,880
What were you saying back there,
that Mama reduced your rent?

713
00:39:20,963 --> 00:39:22,963
- Yes!
- Yes? You liar!

714
00:39:23,046 --> 00:39:26,505
- You think I'd lie about a dead person?
- Mama's not dead. She's alive in here.

715
00:39:26,588 --> 00:39:29,421
Please come quickly.
Something's happened to Shilpa.

716
00:39:29,505 --> 00:39:30,505
- Hey!
- Come.

717
00:39:32,755 --> 00:39:36,796
Mama! You haven't gone anywhere,
Mama. You're still here.

718
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:38,713
- It's an allergic reaction.
- [Shilpa groans]

719
00:39:38,796 --> 00:39:40,546
See this. Look.

720
00:39:40,630 --> 00:39:43,130
- Her skin is turning red.
- My back.

721
00:39:43,213 --> 00:39:45,671
Is she allergic to berries?

722
00:39:46,630 --> 00:39:47,796
Is she?

723
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:49,088
You didn't tell us earlier.

724
00:39:49,171 --> 00:39:51,046
Had we known, we would've told you.

725
00:39:51,130 --> 00:39:52,755
She will survive, right, Doctor?

726
00:39:52,838 --> 00:39:55,421
It's a minor issue. I'll
prescribe some medication. Don't worry.

727
00:39:55,505 --> 00:39:58,296
Oh, please! You'd better take her
to a proper doctor right away.

728
00:39:59,088 --> 00:40:00,088
- Let's go.
- Go. Hurry up.

729
00:40:00,171 --> 00:40:01,713
- Hurry up.
- Come, come.

730
00:40:01,796 --> 00:40:04,296
- Let me know if you need any help, okay?
- Sure. Yes.

731
00:40:04,380 --> 00:40:05,963
- Get some rest.
- Let us know.

732
00:40:06,046 --> 00:40:08,380
Shame on you. Mama…

733
00:40:09,838 --> 00:40:11,005
Let's go.

734
00:41:01,338 --> 00:41:02,338
[Glen] Hey!

735
00:41:23,380 --> 00:41:24,380
Mama?

736
00:41:25,880 --> 00:41:27,171
Is that you, Mama?

737
00:41:29,796 --> 00:41:33,046
I knew you'd come to see me
one last time, Mama.

738
00:41:33,838 --> 00:41:35,005
Am I right, Mama?

739
00:41:36,046 --> 00:41:38,213
I know I made your life
a living hell, Mama.

740
00:41:40,130 --> 00:41:42,421
I was a sinner, Mama. Say it, Mama!

741
00:41:42,505 --> 00:41:45,171
I was a sinner, Mama.
Mama. Please say it, Mama!

742
00:41:45,255 --> 00:41:46,671
- Say it, Mama!
- [mutters]

743
00:41:48,046 --> 00:41:50,380
[in high-pitched voice] I don't want you
to feel guilty about anything.

744
00:41:51,338 --> 00:41:55,005
If you were anyone else's son, you'd still
be a sinner. You'd never be righteous.

745
00:41:55,588 --> 00:41:56,713
Mama.

746
00:41:56,796 --> 00:41:58,088
But I forgive you.

747
00:41:58,671 --> 00:42:00,713
But what happened to your voice, Mama?

748
00:42:01,296 --> 00:42:02,463
My voice…

749
00:42:03,255 --> 00:42:06,546
The damn smoke from your marijuana
ruined my throat, you idiot!

750
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:08,546
I'm sorry, Mama. Sorry, I…

751
00:42:08,630 --> 00:42:11,255
I created so many problems
into your life, Mama.

752
00:42:11,338 --> 00:42:13,755
I'm such a terrible son, Mama.
Good you're dead.

753
00:42:13,838 --> 00:42:15,046
- Go back. Stay dead.
- Okay.

754
00:42:15,130 --> 00:42:16,963
- But, Mama!
- What? What is it?

755
00:42:17,046 --> 00:42:18,088
What?

756
00:42:18,171 --> 00:42:20,005
I want to see your face, Mama.

757
00:42:20,088 --> 00:42:24,046
[stammers] Face? No, no, no. I… I…
I've got a cough.

758
00:42:24,130 --> 00:42:26,921
[coughs] Bad cough.
You'll get a viral infection.

759
00:42:27,005 --> 00:42:29,213
It's okay. I don't care
about viral, COVID, or anything.

760
00:42:29,296 --> 00:42:30,338
I just want to see your face.

761
00:42:30,421 --> 00:42:33,546
- Don't look. My face. I'll…
- I want to see it one last time, Mama.

762
00:42:40,546 --> 00:42:41,755
Mama!

763
00:42:41,838 --> 00:42:43,296
I don't want you to feel bad,

764
00:42:43,380 --> 00:42:46,838
but your face looks like
that idiot Ramakant's face, Mama.

765
00:42:47,630 --> 00:42:48,713
- Yeah!
- No.

766
00:42:49,296 --> 00:42:51,171
What am I even saying, Mama?

767
00:42:51,796 --> 00:42:52,963
Yes.

768
00:42:53,671 --> 00:42:55,380
One last time, Mama.

769
00:42:56,046 --> 00:42:58,171
One last time.
After that, I won't say anything.

770
00:42:58,255 --> 00:43:00,338
- One last request.
- What? What is it?

771
00:43:01,671 --> 00:43:03,463
Can I get a hug, Mama?

772
00:43:03,546 --> 00:43:05,921
Hug? Huh, No, no, I mean…

773
00:43:06,005 --> 00:43:08,880
I never hugged you when I was alive.
How can I hug you now when I'm dead?

774
00:43:08,963 --> 00:43:10,546
- You smell bad.
- I'll finally take a shower

775
00:43:10,630 --> 00:43:12,255
just so we can hug each other, Mama.

776
00:43:12,338 --> 00:43:13,963
Hug? No, no. No hug. No hug.

777
00:43:14,046 --> 00:43:16,296
- Let me hug you just this once.
- What if you squeeze too tight?

778
00:43:16,380 --> 00:43:17,755
Mama, I may never see you again.

779
00:43:17,838 --> 00:43:19,546
- [shouts]
- Let it out, Mama. Yes, Mama.

780
00:43:19,630 --> 00:43:22,338
- I love you. I love you, son.
- I love you. I love you.

781
00:43:25,421 --> 00:43:27,255
- Mama?
- Yes?

782
00:43:27,338 --> 00:43:29,255
What happened to your stomach, Mama?

783
00:43:29,338 --> 00:43:30,421
- [grunts]
- Huh?

784
00:43:32,713 --> 00:43:33,921
Are you pregnant, Mama?

785
00:43:34,921 --> 00:43:36,088
Did you meet Daddy up there?

786
00:43:36,171 --> 00:43:37,505
Huh?

787
00:43:37,588 --> 00:43:39,088
Mama, my brother? I have a brother.

788
00:43:39,171 --> 00:43:40,213
Baby.

789
00:43:41,963 --> 00:43:43,546
- What's that sound, Mama?
- [knocking]

790
00:43:44,421 --> 00:43:45,880
[groans]

791
00:43:45,963 --> 00:43:47,463
I'm really constipated.

792
00:43:47,546 --> 00:43:48,713
What happened to you, Mama?

793
00:43:48,796 --> 00:43:50,255
- Oh, no!
- What's this?

794
00:43:53,338 --> 00:43:55,088
- Mama, this…
- [dramatic music plays]

795
00:43:57,921 --> 00:44:00,380
M-Mama wants to eat toast.

796
00:44:01,880 --> 00:44:03,546
You rascal!

797
00:44:04,130 --> 00:44:06,338
Shame on you! My mom only just died!

798
00:44:06,421 --> 00:44:09,546
- And you're trying to steal.
- Glen. Glen.

799
00:44:09,630 --> 00:44:12,005
This really is my toaster.
Let me take it and go.

800
00:44:12,088 --> 00:44:15,838
You're going to just one place, man.
[shudders] Straight to jail.

801
00:44:15,921 --> 00:44:18,796
I will call the cops,
you bastard! You wait!

802
00:44:19,588 --> 00:44:21,880
Glen! It's my toaster. Give it back!

803
00:44:21,963 --> 00:44:24,588
You're never gonna get it.
You're never gonna get it.

804
00:44:24,671 --> 00:44:26,171
I'm never gonna give it to you.

805
00:44:28,546 --> 00:44:30,380
Try and take it from me! Try!

806
00:44:30,463 --> 00:44:31,463
Freeze!

807
00:44:34,338 --> 00:44:36,671
- Hey! Hey!
- Hey!

808
00:44:36,755 --> 00:44:38,130
[groaning]

809
00:44:41,213 --> 00:44:43,088
- Freeze!
- Get lost.

810
00:44:43,171 --> 00:44:44,255
Hey!

811
00:44:44,338 --> 00:44:46,921
Glen, stop! Give me my toaster!

812
00:44:47,005 --> 00:44:48,338
Give it. Let go! Let go.

813
00:44:48,421 --> 00:44:49,505
[groans]

814
00:44:49,588 --> 00:44:50,755
Let go. Let go of it.

815
00:44:50,838 --> 00:44:52,463
It's my toaster.

816
00:44:52,546 --> 00:44:54,380
My toaster! My toaster!

817
00:44:54,463 --> 00:44:55,463
I won't let it go.

818
00:44:55,546 --> 00:44:58,005
Let go! Let go! Let it go!

819
00:44:58,088 --> 00:45:00,088
[both exclaim]

820
00:45:01,630 --> 00:45:03,380
- [body thuds]
- Huh?

821
00:45:03,463 --> 00:45:05,588
- [breathes shakily]
- [suspenseful music plays]

822
00:45:31,963 --> 00:45:33,046
[groans] Glen?

823
00:45:41,963 --> 00:45:42,963
Glen?

824
00:45:43,630 --> 00:45:44,630
Glen?

825
00:45:48,546 --> 00:45:49,546
[dramatic music plays]

826
00:46:05,796 --> 00:46:07,171
[crying]

827
00:46:34,463 --> 00:46:35,505
Why?

828
00:46:39,880 --> 00:46:41,671
[sobbing]

829
00:46:48,380 --> 00:46:49,838
Hello? Police station.

830
00:46:53,088 --> 00:46:54,296
[sighs]

831
00:46:54,380 --> 00:46:55,380
Hello, ma'am.

832
00:46:56,088 --> 00:46:57,421
[stammers] Ma'am.

833
00:46:57,963 --> 00:46:59,880
Ma'am, I promise, I didn't do anything.

834
00:46:59,963 --> 00:47:04,380
My next-door neighbour, Glen,
I went to his house to pick up my toaster.

835
00:47:04,463 --> 00:47:05,546
It's my toaster, ma'am.

836
00:47:05,630 --> 00:47:08,546
But he's a total junkie, ma'am.
He refused to give it back.

837
00:47:08,630 --> 00:47:11,088
So we had a little pushing
and shoving, and…

838
00:47:11,171 --> 00:47:13,713
suddenly, he-he fell
over from the balcony, ma'am.

839
00:47:13,796 --> 00:47:16,796
And… And he died, ma'am.

840
00:47:16,880 --> 00:47:20,171
But it wasn't my fault, ma'am.
I swear on my mom, I didn't do anything.

841
00:47:20,255 --> 00:47:21,255
[breathes shakily]

842
00:47:22,130 --> 00:47:25,130
- Hello? Hello?
- Believe me, sir, I didn't steal anything.

843
00:47:25,213 --> 00:47:27,421
Why are you wasting my time?
Just let me go.

844
00:47:27,505 --> 00:47:29,338
- Hey! Are you trying to act smart?
- Yeah?

845
00:47:29,421 --> 00:47:31,630
Stealing your neighbour's flower pots?

846
00:47:32,213 --> 00:47:33,338
Do one thing.

847
00:47:33,421 --> 00:47:37,255
Strip him naked, and slap his
stealing ass with a wet slipper.

848
00:47:37,338 --> 00:47:39,421
- Get out of here!
- Move. Move it!

849
00:47:40,255 --> 00:47:41,338
[sighs]

850
00:47:41,421 --> 00:47:43,505
Hello? Sorry. Tell me.

851
00:47:43,588 --> 00:47:44,838
[gasps]

852
00:47:45,713 --> 00:47:46,796
Hello?

853
00:47:47,588 --> 00:47:49,046
Hello? Speak up.

854
00:47:49,130 --> 00:47:51,255
I'm calling from
the credit card company, ma'am.

855
00:47:51,338 --> 00:47:53,588
We have this credit card scheme
for you, and…

856
00:47:53,671 --> 00:47:54,671
[clicks]

857
00:48:09,838 --> 00:48:11,171
[creaking]

858
00:48:28,255 --> 00:48:30,505
[phone rings]

859
00:48:31,671 --> 00:48:33,630
- Yeah, tell me?
- Where are you?

860
00:48:33,713 --> 00:48:35,171
You left so early this morning.

861
00:48:35,255 --> 00:48:37,213
Yes, I had to pick up something
from Guddu.

862
00:48:37,296 --> 00:48:38,755
Do you know Glen is dead?

863
00:48:38,838 --> 00:48:40,130
Yeah.

864
00:48:40,213 --> 00:48:42,755
Yeah? How do you know he's dead?

865
00:48:43,505 --> 00:48:47,630
Yeah. [stammers] I mean, yeah.
What? G-Glen is dead?

866
00:48:47,713 --> 00:48:50,505
- Yeah?
- Yeah. I don't know how it happened.

867
00:48:50,588 --> 00:48:52,296
Must've fallen off the balcony,
poor fellow.

868
00:48:53,005 --> 00:48:56,338
Huh? How do you know
he fell off the balcony?

869
00:48:56,421 --> 00:49:01,046
Well, he… he was always stoned, so maybe
he fell… he really fell off?

870
00:49:01,130 --> 00:49:02,630
Yeah.

871
00:49:03,380 --> 00:49:04,421
Could've been suicide.

872
00:49:05,255 --> 00:49:06,338
Or maybe murder.

873
00:49:06,421 --> 00:49:09,296
Murder? M-Murder? Why murder?
Why would it be a murder?

874
00:49:09,380 --> 00:49:10,796
You keep talking nonsense!

875
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:13,880
You better stop watching those
crappy TV shows, okay?

876
00:49:13,963 --> 00:49:16,255
And please… please stay home.

877
00:49:16,338 --> 00:49:17,963
When the police land up there,
don't get involved.

878
00:49:18,046 --> 00:49:19,505
Yeah. Fine.

879
00:49:20,380 --> 00:49:22,588
Why would it be a murder? Hmm.

880
00:49:25,130 --> 00:49:26,130
Hi, sir!

881
00:49:26,671 --> 00:49:29,046
- Here so early in the morning!
- Yeah.

882
00:49:29,130 --> 00:49:30,630
- Come on then.
- Yeah.

883
00:49:32,088 --> 00:49:33,546
I brought it back in one day.

884
00:49:34,296 --> 00:49:35,671
But sir, where's the box?

885
00:49:37,463 --> 00:49:39,755
You don't need the box to toast bread.
I brought the toaster, right?

886
00:49:39,838 --> 00:49:40,921
[chuckles]

887
00:49:41,713 --> 00:49:45,213
Yes, sir, but then used products
have a no-return policy.

888
00:49:45,296 --> 00:49:46,755
I hope you haven't used it?

889
00:49:46,838 --> 00:49:49,296
No. Not at all.
I just took it out of the box. That's all.

890
00:49:49,380 --> 00:49:50,755
- You sure, sir?
- Yeah, yeah.

891
00:49:55,880 --> 00:49:58,755
This is probably
when you gave us a demonstration.

892
00:49:58,838 --> 00:50:01,130
You toasted bread for us.
We haven't used it.

893
00:50:01,213 --> 00:50:03,671
This can be cleaned. I'll dust it off.
[blows] There's nothing.

894
00:50:03,755 --> 00:50:05,671
Just crumbs. See? There, it's all gone.

895
00:50:05,755 --> 00:50:08,046
You can have it back.
And please, return my money.

896
00:50:11,546 --> 00:50:13,505
- It's from…
- No, sir, it doesn't…

897
00:50:13,588 --> 00:50:15,755
Look, I'm a salesman.
You're also a salesman.

898
00:50:15,838 --> 00:50:17,171
Right? Don't say no more.

899
00:50:17,255 --> 00:50:19,838
Take this. Buy some candy
for your kids. From an older brother.

900
00:50:19,921 --> 00:50:21,421
Now could you hurry? I gotta go, please.

901
00:50:21,505 --> 00:50:23,255
TEN RUPEES

902
00:50:23,338 --> 00:50:24,588
RESERVE BANK OF INDIA

903
00:50:27,046 --> 00:50:28,338
[grunts]

904
00:50:30,213 --> 00:50:32,796
- [groans]
- Take your toaster and get out of here!

905
00:50:34,171 --> 00:50:36,380
- Damn fool.
- I'll take all of you to court!

906
00:50:46,880 --> 00:50:48,171
[phone chimes]

907
00:50:59,963 --> 00:51:01,088
[gasping]

908
00:51:23,213 --> 00:51:27,713
WHO ARE YOU? WHAT DO YOU WANT?

909
00:51:27,796 --> 00:51:29,046
SEEN

910
00:51:29,130 --> 00:51:33,380
WAIT. YOU'LL FIND OUT.

911
00:51:45,588 --> 00:51:47,630
- [suspenseful music plays]
- [whistling]

912
00:52:11,338 --> 00:52:12,463
Hey!

913
00:52:13,463 --> 00:52:14,546
Who are you?

914
00:52:16,171 --> 00:52:17,421
- Hey!
- [whistling stops]

915
00:52:17,505 --> 00:52:18,505
Who are you?

916
00:52:21,421 --> 00:52:22,505
You are?

917
00:52:22,588 --> 00:52:24,338
Tenant of the family.

918
00:52:24,421 --> 00:52:26,005
The people who used to live here.

919
00:52:26,088 --> 00:52:28,505
They're up there. [laughs]

920
00:52:28,588 --> 00:52:31,088
Now you can happily claim everything.

921
00:52:32,921 --> 00:52:33,921
He's alive.

922
00:52:34,005 --> 00:52:35,338
What is this nonsense?

923
00:52:35,421 --> 00:52:37,421
Who are you?
And what the hell are you doing here?

924
00:52:37,505 --> 00:52:40,296
I'm talking to you, mister.
Do you hear me?

925
00:52:40,380 --> 00:52:41,380
Hello?

926
00:52:41,463 --> 00:52:43,338
Hey? Why are you yelling?

927
00:52:44,296 --> 00:52:45,838
Jai Hind, sir!

928
00:52:45,921 --> 00:52:46,921
He's our chief.

929
00:52:50,421 --> 00:52:51,963
Yes, Salunke?

930
00:52:53,630 --> 00:52:54,713
How did he die?

931
00:52:54,796 --> 00:52:57,046
Sir, it's either suicide or an accident.

932
00:52:57,130 --> 00:52:58,838
His mother passed away just a day before.

933
00:52:58,921 --> 00:53:00,588
Hmm.

934
00:53:00,671 --> 00:53:01,796
Drugs.

935
00:53:02,588 --> 00:53:05,171
He used drugs, sir. So maybe an accident.

936
00:53:05,255 --> 00:53:06,963
Oh-ho!

937
00:53:07,046 --> 00:53:09,255
You could sense it
even at his mother's funeral.

938
00:53:10,546 --> 00:53:12,588
The grim reaper hasn't left yet.

939
00:53:12,671 --> 00:53:16,338
Why would the grim reaper
go anywhere else, huh?

940
00:53:16,421 --> 00:53:19,296
Calculate the average age
in this apartment complex.

941
00:53:19,380 --> 00:53:22,796
He probably meets his sales target
right here.

942
00:53:22,880 --> 00:53:24,921
Excuse me, please.

943
00:53:26,255 --> 00:53:27,838
[whistling]

944
00:53:35,380 --> 00:53:36,463
[tuts]

945
00:53:37,171 --> 00:53:40,630
Mrs D'Souza's precious
toaster got left behind.

946
00:53:40,713 --> 00:53:41,880
[chuckles]

947
00:53:43,130 --> 00:53:44,213
Pichkoo!

948
00:53:45,338 --> 00:53:46,713
Pichkoo!

949
00:53:46,796 --> 00:53:47,880
Pich…

950
00:53:48,921 --> 00:53:50,046
Where is it?

951
00:53:52,880 --> 00:53:55,755
Wow! What an awesome sticker, that is!

952
00:53:55,838 --> 00:53:57,255
Pichkoo!

953
00:53:58,838 --> 00:54:00,421
Salunke!

954
00:54:01,796 --> 00:54:02,838
Has anything…

955
00:54:04,088 --> 00:54:05,796
been stolen from the house?

956
00:54:05,880 --> 00:54:06,880
No, sir.

957
00:54:08,713 --> 00:54:10,338
Anything missing from the kitchen?

958
00:54:11,380 --> 00:54:16,296
I mean, like a new mixer, toaster,
something like that?

959
00:54:16,380 --> 00:54:18,338
What kind of a thief
would only steal a toaster?

960
00:54:18,421 --> 00:54:19,588
Did I ask you?

961
00:54:21,213 --> 00:54:24,213
Sir, this house
has never seen a new toaster.

962
00:54:24,296 --> 00:54:28,421
All these years, Mrs D'Souza makes her
toast in this same toaster.

963
00:54:29,463 --> 00:54:30,546
Made.

964
00:54:30,630 --> 00:54:32,713
Oh, Salunke! It's a crime scene.

965
00:54:33,421 --> 00:54:36,671
Not the community club where everyone
shows up to play cards.

966
00:54:36,755 --> 00:54:37,880
Get them out. Out! Out!

967
00:54:37,963 --> 00:54:38,963
- Move it, everyone.
- Out!

968
00:54:39,046 --> 00:54:40,588
Everyone out!

969
00:54:40,671 --> 00:54:42,630
Move it, madam!

970
00:54:42,713 --> 00:54:43,796
Everybody out.

971
00:54:45,796 --> 00:54:47,296
What about you?

972
00:54:47,380 --> 00:54:49,130
Do you need someone to escort you?

973
00:54:49,213 --> 00:54:50,838
Out!

974
00:54:50,921 --> 00:54:52,171
Mr Burma.

975
00:54:52,255 --> 00:54:54,463
Let's go.
You can take your nap in the park.

976
00:55:02,880 --> 00:55:04,755
[line ringing]

977
00:55:07,213 --> 00:55:08,713
[phone ringing]

978
00:55:10,546 --> 00:55:11,630
Talk to me.

979
00:55:11,713 --> 00:55:14,713
That junkie's phone, laptop,
hard disk, everything

980
00:55:14,796 --> 00:55:17,421
they've been taken into custody.
I'll personally check everything.

981
00:55:17,505 --> 00:55:20,630
But, sir, the last time, I mean…

982
00:55:20,713 --> 00:55:23,963
The last time when I met him for
the first time, he had a toaster with him.

983
00:55:24,046 --> 00:55:26,130
He was clinging to it and walking around.

984
00:55:26,213 --> 00:55:28,838
- That toaster is missing.
- Listen…

985
00:55:28,921 --> 00:55:29,921
[inhales sharply]

986
00:55:30,005 --> 00:55:33,713
Before someone else gets their hands
on it, I want that video. Understand?

987
00:55:33,796 --> 00:55:37,421
Hey, hey. No need to stress, sir.
I'll find it.

988
00:55:37,505 --> 00:55:39,338
Just don't forget my ticket…

989
00:55:39,421 --> 00:55:40,671
[line beeping]

990
00:55:40,755 --> 00:55:41,963
He hung up.

991
00:55:45,421 --> 00:55:48,255
Murder, isn't it? I think so too.

992
00:55:48,338 --> 00:55:49,338
Hey.

993
00:55:50,088 --> 00:55:51,796
Stop watching crime shows on TV.

994
00:55:51,880 --> 00:55:55,130
Better than that,
watch cooking shows. Okay?

995
00:55:55,213 --> 00:55:56,213
Now go.

996
00:55:56,838 --> 00:55:58,546
My TV. My choice of shows.

997
00:55:58,630 --> 00:55:59,630
Hey?

998
00:56:03,130 --> 00:56:04,213
Aggressive.

999
00:56:20,213 --> 00:56:21,338
[phone chimes]

1000
00:56:27,755 --> 00:56:28,963
B-206.

1001
00:56:32,546 --> 00:56:33,546
Mrs Pherwani?

1002
00:56:39,671 --> 00:56:40,921
Mrs Pherwani?

1003
00:56:46,671 --> 00:56:47,713
Mrs Pherwani?

1004
00:56:55,546 --> 00:56:56,671
It's me, Ramakant.

1005
00:57:18,838 --> 00:57:19,880
Mrs Pherwani?

1006
00:57:22,380 --> 00:57:24,588
Are you there? Namaste, Mrs Pherwani.

1007
00:57:25,713 --> 00:57:28,713
It's not at all
what it looks like in the video.

1008
00:57:29,546 --> 00:57:31,380
[Pherwani] Wait.

1009
00:57:33,088 --> 00:57:35,713
Oh, okay, okay, Mrs Pherwani.
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

1010
00:57:35,796 --> 00:57:37,796
Uh, sorry. Bad manners.

1011
00:57:37,880 --> 00:57:39,671
You shouldn't disturb anyone
while they're on the pot.

1012
00:57:39,755 --> 00:57:41,755
I had no idea. You carry on.

1013
00:57:41,838 --> 00:57:45,130
Be comfortable. Take your time.
Let it all out. I'll wait right here.

1014
00:57:45,213 --> 00:57:46,546
I'll wait till you're done.

1015
00:57:48,171 --> 00:57:51,588
But what you're seeing in the video,
it's not like that at all.

1016
00:57:51,671 --> 00:57:53,796
Why don't you watch it again, carefully?

1017
00:57:53,880 --> 00:57:56,713
And anyway, you knew Glen, right?
That alcoholic junkie.

1018
00:57:56,796 --> 00:57:59,713
I swear he was drunk even then.
He lost his balance and fell over.

1019
00:57:59,796 --> 00:58:01,921
I didn't do anything. Believe me.

1020
00:58:03,046 --> 00:58:05,213
There's so much stress in my life already.

1021
00:58:06,088 --> 00:58:09,630
Shilpa's getting her IVF done.
Mrs D'Souza must've told you.

1022
00:58:09,713 --> 00:58:13,671
She's having trouble getting pregnant.
It's very stressful.

1023
00:58:13,755 --> 00:58:15,963
[Pherwani] It's possible you
could be the problem.

1024
00:58:16,046 --> 00:58:19,255
No, no, not at all. It's not me.
My tests are all fine.

1025
00:58:19,338 --> 00:58:22,880
The doctor said
I'm a roaring lion, actually.

1026
00:58:22,963 --> 00:58:24,088
But Shilpa, poor thing.

1027
00:58:24,171 --> 00:58:26,755
[Pherwani] Good. Don't disturb me now.

1028
00:58:26,838 --> 00:58:29,630
You see the room on the right?
Go wait for me in there.

1029
00:58:31,796 --> 00:58:33,463
- In the room?
- Yes.

1030
00:58:34,421 --> 00:58:35,421
Okay, I'll do that.

1031
00:58:37,380 --> 00:58:40,630
Also please don't offer me tea
or anything. I don't drink tea this late.

1032
00:59:06,755 --> 00:59:10,338
Next station, coming up. Doors will open…

1033
00:59:10,421 --> 00:59:11,671
[romantic music plays]

1034
00:59:31,005 --> 00:59:32,046
[shouts]

1035
00:59:32,880 --> 00:59:33,921
Eh?

1036
00:59:34,630 --> 00:59:36,046
[groans]

1037
00:59:36,130 --> 00:59:37,338
Mrs Pherwani!

1038
01:00:05,713 --> 01:00:06,880
Mrs Pherwani!

1039
01:00:07,755 --> 01:00:09,296
[shouting]

1040
01:00:09,380 --> 01:00:11,588
- What are you doing?
- [upbeat music plays]

1041
01:00:22,546 --> 01:00:24,296
- [coughs]
- Mrs Pherwani.

1042
01:00:24,921 --> 01:00:27,255
Please let me go. Please delete my video.

1043
01:00:29,796 --> 01:00:33,088
It's been 20 years
since Mr Pherwani died.

1044
01:00:34,171 --> 01:00:38,713
This bed has stayed cold and dry
since then. Just like Malini's heart.

1045
01:00:39,380 --> 01:00:41,046
You know that D'Souza?

1046
01:00:41,713 --> 01:00:44,171
She was Malini's best friend.

1047
01:00:46,296 --> 01:00:48,671
But Malini was very jealous of her.

1048
01:00:50,046 --> 01:00:52,463
Because you were so close to her.

1049
01:00:54,088 --> 01:00:55,255
Bitch.

1050
01:00:56,421 --> 01:00:57,755
Oh.

1051
01:00:57,838 --> 01:00:59,046
[sighs]

1052
01:01:00,213 --> 01:01:05,005
But now you'll be close only to Malini.

1053
01:01:07,088 --> 01:01:09,046
Look at Malini.

1054
01:01:09,130 --> 01:01:11,588
- My teddy bear.
- [grunts] Ew!

1055
01:01:11,671 --> 01:01:13,713
Please. Please don't do this.

1056
01:01:14,338 --> 01:01:16,755
- Please. Please let me explain myself.
- [grunts]

1057
01:01:16,838 --> 01:01:18,421
See. I-I lied to you.

1058
01:01:18,505 --> 01:01:21,338
There's nothing wrong with Shilpa. She's
more than good. She's perfectly fine.

1059
01:01:21,421 --> 01:01:23,463
I'm the one with problems.

1060
01:01:23,546 --> 01:01:25,296
Please. I'm no lion or anything.
I'm a mouse.

1061
01:01:25,380 --> 01:01:27,463
You're like an aunty to me.
Aunty, please delete it.

1062
01:01:27,546 --> 01:01:28,546
Who aunty?

1063
01:01:29,130 --> 01:01:31,213
There is no aunty in here.

1064
01:01:32,088 --> 01:01:33,921
There is only Malini.

1065
01:01:34,005 --> 01:01:38,088
Malini. Call me Malini.

1066
01:01:39,463 --> 01:01:40,671
Or better still,

1067
01:01:41,588 --> 01:01:43,796
call me "Maal."

1068
01:01:43,880 --> 01:01:45,171
[gulps]

1069
01:01:45,255 --> 01:01:46,713
"Maal"?

1070
01:01:48,255 --> 01:01:50,755
[stammers] Maal, please.

1071
01:01:50,838 --> 01:01:54,296
Maal. Maal, please.
I'll do all your work around the house.

1072
01:01:54,380 --> 01:01:56,588
A lifetime full time housemaid for free.

1073
01:01:56,671 --> 01:01:58,255
I'll vacuum under the bed twice a week.

1074
01:01:58,338 --> 01:02:00,005
Do you wear diapers?
I'll bring you diapers.

1075
01:02:00,088 --> 01:02:02,296
- I'll clean your toilet.
- Shush.

1076
01:02:02,380 --> 01:02:03,588
Delete it, please.

1077
01:02:13,880 --> 01:02:16,588
- There. Video deleted.
- [chimes]

1078
01:02:17,255 --> 01:02:19,921
Now go. Get out.

1079
01:02:20,005 --> 01:02:24,046
Thank you. Thank you, Mrs Pherwani.
Thank you. Thank you.

1080
01:02:24,130 --> 01:02:27,046
- I'll be here tomorrow as promised.
- [remote chimes]

1081
01:02:33,671 --> 01:02:37,171
Malini always has a backup ready.

1082
01:02:44,255 --> 01:02:46,171
[stammers] Time-out, please.

1083
01:02:47,963 --> 01:02:49,338
Mrs Pherwani, this…

1084
01:02:49,421 --> 01:02:51,213
This is my toaster.

1085
01:02:53,880 --> 01:02:54,921
Brand new.

1086
01:02:55,546 --> 01:03:00,338
I have paid 9,000 for it.
But I'll give it to you for 4,999. Only.

1087
01:03:00,963 --> 01:03:03,630
Special price for a special lady.

1088
01:03:04,463 --> 01:03:05,546
For Maal aunty.

1089
01:03:06,505 --> 01:03:09,755
Malini will consider
this a gift and keep it.

1090
01:03:10,255 --> 01:03:11,421
Gift?

1091
01:03:13,213 --> 01:03:14,296
[gasps]

1092
01:03:14,380 --> 01:03:16,046
And you too.

1093
01:03:16,671 --> 01:03:18,588
Huh? [exclaims]

1094
01:03:21,130 --> 01:03:22,421
[sighs]

1095
01:03:45,130 --> 01:03:46,171
- You're back home?
- [gasps]

1096
01:03:46,255 --> 01:03:47,588
[breathes heavily]

1097
01:03:47,671 --> 01:03:48,880
Why are you bouncing on me?

1098
01:03:48,963 --> 01:03:51,755
I have something to tell you.
I just couldn't sleep at all.

1099
01:03:52,421 --> 01:03:55,005
Do you have the slightest idea
what's going on in this complex?

1100
01:03:56,880 --> 01:03:57,963
What else is going on?

1101
01:03:59,171 --> 01:04:00,338
There's been a murder.

1102
01:04:01,505 --> 01:04:02,755
Glen's murder.

1103
01:04:02,838 --> 01:04:05,505
- M-M-Murder?
- Mm-hmm.

1104
01:04:05,588 --> 01:04:08,921
That cop who came in earlier… I overheard
him talking to someone on the phone.

1105
01:04:09,005 --> 01:04:10,963
He said Glen's toaster is missing.

1106
01:04:11,921 --> 01:04:13,421
From the way they were speaking,

1107
01:04:13,505 --> 01:04:16,130
I felt that the murder took place
because of that same toaster.

1108
01:04:16,213 --> 01:04:17,255
Huh?

1109
01:04:18,046 --> 01:04:22,338
T-Toaster? Murder? What is
this nonsense you're babbling about?

1110
01:04:23,255 --> 01:04:25,505
Would someone murder a man
over a silly toaster?

1111
01:04:26,296 --> 01:04:29,463
Everyone's saying it's a suicide,
and here you have your own theories.

1112
01:04:29,546 --> 01:04:30,588
No.

1113
01:04:31,505 --> 01:04:35,171
And what I also feel was that
Mrs D'Souza was also a victim of murder.

1114
01:04:35,921 --> 01:04:38,130
Hey, hey. Shilpa, listen.

1115
01:04:38,213 --> 01:04:41,130
For God's sake, don't say things
like this in front of anyone else.

1116
01:04:41,213 --> 01:04:43,796
Because of you, the cops will come
and throw me into jail.

1117
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:46,213
Huh?
Why will the cops throw you into jail?

1118
01:04:47,130 --> 01:04:49,171
If the wife is spreading rumours,

1119
01:04:49,255 --> 01:04:52,088
then obviously the husband
will bear the brunt of it.

1120
01:04:52,171 --> 01:04:53,796
- Hmm. So this is a rumour?
- Right?

1121
01:04:54,796 --> 01:04:57,880
It's a rumour? Fine. Fine.
Don't believe what I'm saying.

1122
01:05:00,463 --> 01:05:02,463
When he finally gets caught,
we'll talk then.

1123
01:05:03,588 --> 01:05:04,838
Caught? Who?

1124
01:05:05,630 --> 01:05:07,088
Who'll be caught?

1125
01:05:07,171 --> 01:05:08,755
The toaster killer.

1126
01:05:12,588 --> 01:05:14,713
- The toaster killer?
- Hmm.

1127
01:05:16,171 --> 01:05:18,463
How can you just give someone
a label like that?

1128
01:05:19,463 --> 01:05:20,463
I mean…

1129
01:05:21,338 --> 01:05:23,838
Who knows? Maybe the poor guy
just couldn't help it.

1130
01:05:25,380 --> 01:05:29,255
C-Can you imagine
what he must be going through?

1131
01:05:30,130 --> 01:05:31,588
- But who?
- The…

1132
01:05:33,963 --> 01:05:37,296
This, uh… [stammers] …toaster killer,
the one you just mentioned.

1133
01:05:38,046 --> 01:05:39,630
What he's going through?

1134
01:05:40,255 --> 01:05:42,296
Just wait till he goes to jail.

1135
01:05:42,380 --> 01:05:45,546
When they strip him naked
and hang him face down.

1136
01:05:45,630 --> 01:05:50,005
And the police will whip his ass
with a slipper soaked in water.

1137
01:05:50,088 --> 01:05:52,796
- Whack! Whack.
- Hey!

1138
01:05:52,880 --> 01:05:55,255
- That's it.
- How can you say things like that?

1139
01:05:57,296 --> 01:05:58,380
Why are you so worried?

1140
01:05:58,963 --> 01:06:00,963
I saw this on that crime show on TV.

1141
01:06:02,421 --> 01:06:06,380
Shilpa, how I wish…

1142
01:06:07,796 --> 01:06:12,088
For your own sake, you'll stop
watching those ridiculous crime shows.

1143
01:06:12,171 --> 01:06:13,255
- Please.
- [clicks tongue]

1144
01:06:20,463 --> 01:06:22,838
But why do the slippers have to be soaked?

1145
01:06:23,796 --> 01:06:24,963
Because it stings more.

1146
01:06:25,963 --> 01:06:27,463
- Hmm.
- Whack!

1147
01:06:36,796 --> 01:06:39,713
- [heartbeat thumping]
- [smacks]

1148
01:06:39,796 --> 01:06:40,880
[shudders]

1149
01:06:40,963 --> 01:06:42,671
[thumping continues]

1150
01:06:48,380 --> 01:06:50,046
[phone ringing]

1151
01:06:57,421 --> 01:06:59,463
[ringing continues in distance]

1152
01:07:03,130 --> 01:07:04,630
Hey.

1153
01:07:04,713 --> 01:07:07,630
Why aren't you answering?
Usually, you run out naked to answer.

1154
01:07:08,505 --> 01:07:09,546
[chuckles]

1155
01:07:09,630 --> 01:07:10,880
[ringing continues]

1156
01:07:16,838 --> 01:07:17,963
Hello.

1157
01:07:19,046 --> 01:07:20,921
- Hello?
- [Pherwani] Since last night…

1158
01:07:21,005 --> 01:07:23,046
I don't wanna talk about
that nightmare at all.

1159
01:07:23,130 --> 01:07:24,588
All right, then.

1160
01:07:24,671 --> 01:07:27,921
Maybe the cops will talk to you
once they've seen the video.

1161
01:07:28,005 --> 01:07:30,838
[grunts] Aren't you too old
to be blackmailing young people?

1162
01:07:30,921 --> 01:07:32,630
Have some fear of God.

1163
01:07:33,505 --> 01:07:35,088
What do… What do you want anyway?

1164
01:07:35,171 --> 01:07:38,046
- Patience, my teddy bear.
- [chuckles]

1165
01:07:38,130 --> 01:07:39,213
Yeah, Guddu.

1166
01:07:39,296 --> 01:07:40,796
[chuckles]

1167
01:07:40,880 --> 01:07:45,130
When you come to see me next,
please wear that jazzy red tracksuit.

1168
01:07:45,880 --> 01:07:47,921
Tonight. Okay?

1169
01:07:48,005 --> 01:07:50,796
Yeah, cool, Guddu. I'll see you
later tonight. [chuckles]

1170
01:07:50,880 --> 01:07:53,005
- [chuckles] Guddu.
- [chuckles]

1171
01:07:53,088 --> 01:07:54,171
Namaste.

1172
01:07:55,838 --> 01:07:56,838
[chuckles]

1173
01:07:56,921 --> 01:07:59,380
So after Mrs D'Souza,
she's become your new buddy?

1174
01:07:59,463 --> 01:08:00,963
[chuckles]

1175
01:08:02,130 --> 01:08:03,213
Shame on you.

1176
01:08:10,171 --> 01:08:11,421
[door closes]

1177
01:08:14,588 --> 01:08:15,713
Huh?

1178
01:08:15,796 --> 01:08:16,796
[sighs]

1179
01:08:21,213 --> 01:08:22,713
Ramu!

1180
01:08:22,796 --> 01:08:25,546
My red teddy bear!

1181
01:08:25,630 --> 01:08:27,296
Namaste.

1182
01:08:36,963 --> 01:08:38,421
[sneezes]

1183
01:08:54,588 --> 01:08:55,588
[moaning]

1184
01:08:58,796 --> 01:09:01,380
Ah, yes, yes, yes.

1185
01:09:12,880 --> 01:09:14,046
What happened?

1186
01:09:14,130 --> 01:09:15,630
I'm just a little tired.

1187
01:09:15,713 --> 01:09:17,005
Climbed a mountain?

1188
01:09:17,088 --> 01:09:18,921
A mountain climbed on me.

1189
01:09:27,255 --> 01:09:28,838
Come and get me.

1190
01:09:41,796 --> 01:09:45,630
If I become Deputy CM tomorrow and if
people catch me in a threesome,

1191
01:09:45,713 --> 01:09:46,796
how do you think that will look?

1192
01:09:46,880 --> 01:09:48,171
- It'll look bad. Very bad.
- Yeah?

1193
01:09:48,255 --> 01:09:49,796
It's not going to look good, right?

1194
01:09:49,880 --> 01:09:51,546
Yeah. Very bad, for sure.

1195
01:09:51,630 --> 01:09:54,296
- Get me the video.
- Mmm. I'll get it.

1196
01:09:54,380 --> 01:09:56,588
Do what needs to be done.

1197
01:09:56,671 --> 01:09:58,213
- Burn him alive, if need be.
- Okay.

1198
01:09:58,296 --> 01:09:59,755
- Kill him if you have to.
- Okay.

1199
01:10:07,213 --> 01:10:08,671
[phone ringing]

1200
01:10:20,880 --> 01:10:22,380
[gasps]

1201
01:10:23,046 --> 01:10:25,130
- [stammers]
- [laughs]

1202
01:10:26,005 --> 01:10:27,130
Hello?

1203
01:10:27,671 --> 01:10:29,255
Yeah? Where are you?

1204
01:10:30,505 --> 01:10:32,046
Uh, I'm stuck somewhere.

1205
01:10:35,505 --> 01:10:36,546
Right.

1206
01:10:36,630 --> 01:10:39,088
Okay, okay, okay. Come quickly. Okay.

1207
01:10:59,338 --> 01:11:03,838
I hope you're not allergic
to berries, are you?

1208
01:11:25,755 --> 01:11:27,338
- [inspector] Namaste.
- [Amre] Yes, namaste, Timmy.

1209
01:11:27,421 --> 01:11:29,463
We checked the laptop, hard disk.

1210
01:11:29,546 --> 01:11:30,630
- Everything.
- Anything?

1211
01:11:30,713 --> 01:11:31,963
- It's nowhere in sight.
- What?

1212
01:11:32,046 --> 01:11:35,963
I'm quite sure that video of yours
is hidden inside that toaster.

1213
01:11:36,046 --> 01:11:39,671
Your content is so sizzling, after all,
it's probably getting toasted.

1214
01:11:39,755 --> 01:11:41,963
But you know which toaster it is?
Do you, or not?

1215
01:11:42,046 --> 01:11:44,463
- Y-Yes, yes, sir. I know.
- So then?

1216
01:11:44,546 --> 01:11:45,796
I saw it with him, sir.

1217
01:11:45,880 --> 01:11:48,546
It had this yellow sticker with
the name Pichkoo written on it.

1218
01:11:48,630 --> 01:11:49,796
- Then go look for it.
- Don't worry.

1219
01:11:49,880 --> 01:11:53,005
I'll find it. One hundred percent.
I promise!

1220
01:11:53,630 --> 01:11:54,963
But, sir.

1221
01:11:55,046 --> 01:11:57,463
I hope you remember your promise too?

1222
01:11:57,546 --> 01:11:59,046
Those Disneyland tickets…

1223
01:11:59,130 --> 01:12:00,796
[line beeping]

1224
01:12:02,630 --> 01:12:04,880
[kisses] My teddy bear.

1225
01:12:04,963 --> 01:12:06,255
See you tomorrow.

1226
01:12:15,255 --> 01:12:16,380
[dramatic music]

1227
01:12:31,171 --> 01:12:34,921
Are you checking out your own
pictures secretly, huh?

1228
01:12:36,338 --> 01:12:38,505
Or looking for that video?

1229
01:12:39,505 --> 01:12:40,630
It's not in there.

1230
01:12:47,005 --> 01:12:50,213
[door opens, closes]

1231
01:13:04,296 --> 01:13:05,338
[groans]

1232
01:13:27,171 --> 01:13:29,921
WHAT EXACTLY IS IN THE TOASTER?

1233
01:13:31,546 --> 01:13:33,046
Toaster kill…

1234
01:13:34,005 --> 01:13:36,046
[breathes shakily]

1235
01:13:40,713 --> 01:13:41,838
Shil… Shilpa.

1236
01:13:41,921 --> 01:13:42,921
Hmm?

1237
01:13:43,505 --> 01:13:45,921
I-I have something to tell you.

1238
01:13:46,005 --> 01:13:47,588
Yeah, tell me.

1239
01:13:52,463 --> 01:13:53,921
I…

1240
01:13:54,005 --> 01:13:55,546
I…

1241
01:13:58,046 --> 01:13:59,171
I…

1242
01:14:01,005 --> 01:14:02,130
I…

1243
01:14:05,088 --> 01:14:06,171
[groans]

1244
01:14:08,338 --> 01:14:10,671
Where… Where did this come from?

1245
01:14:10,755 --> 01:14:12,671
Mrs Pherwani sent it.

1246
01:14:12,755 --> 01:14:13,963
Your new friend.

1247
01:14:16,171 --> 01:14:18,421
What's wrong? Everything okay?

1248
01:14:18,505 --> 01:14:20,630
- No, it's nothing.
- Okay.

1249
01:14:20,713 --> 01:14:22,838
Could you spread this
on the bread for me, please?

1250
01:14:32,380 --> 01:14:33,921
[Pherwani] Ramu!

1251
01:14:34,005 --> 01:14:35,838
[laughter]

1252
01:14:45,880 --> 01:14:47,713
[man] Aren't you ashamed?

1253
01:14:56,838 --> 01:14:58,171
Whack!

1254
01:14:59,171 --> 01:15:00,963
[people chattering, laughing]

1255
01:15:20,380 --> 01:15:23,130
- [crowd chanting] Kill him! Kill him!
- Whack!

1256
01:15:34,671 --> 01:15:36,838
[crowd continues chanting]

1257
01:15:39,796 --> 01:15:41,630
[screaming]

1258
01:15:42,380 --> 01:15:43,880
[gasps]

1259
01:15:43,963 --> 01:15:45,630
[breathes heavily]

1260
01:15:48,671 --> 01:15:49,880
[gulps]

1261
01:16:00,505 --> 01:16:02,005
[phone ringing]

1262
01:16:09,171 --> 01:16:10,796
- What is it?
- Ramu.

1263
01:16:10,880 --> 01:16:13,880
See you tonight at 09:30.

1264
01:16:13,963 --> 01:16:16,713
Sorry, I can't come over tonight.

1265
01:16:17,380 --> 01:16:19,255
This evening, I'm going out with Shilpa.

1266
01:16:19,838 --> 01:16:21,671
And anyway, I'm exhausted.

1267
01:16:21,755 --> 01:16:24,005
By the time I get home,
it's three in the morning.

1268
01:16:24,088 --> 01:16:26,005
I've been lying to Shilpa the whole time.

1269
01:16:26,088 --> 01:16:27,296
I can't do this anymore.

1270
01:16:28,671 --> 01:16:29,838
Can't do this?

1271
01:16:29,921 --> 01:16:31,338
No.

1272
01:16:31,421 --> 01:16:32,963
Then do one thing.

1273
01:16:33,046 --> 01:16:34,171
Leave Shilpa for good.

1274
01:16:34,255 --> 01:16:37,171
What? Have you lost your mind?

1275
01:16:37,255 --> 01:16:40,088
She's my wife, okay?
I… I love her very much.

1276
01:16:40,755 --> 01:16:42,505
Oh. So you love her?

1277
01:16:42,588 --> 01:16:44,005
Yes.

1278
01:16:44,088 --> 01:16:46,713
Then you'll have to pay the price
for that love, Ramu.

1279
01:16:46,796 --> 01:16:48,755
What… what price?

1280
01:16:49,421 --> 01:16:50,713
Fifty lakhs.

1281
01:16:50,796 --> 01:16:52,130
[scoffs]

1282
01:16:52,213 --> 01:16:54,796
Mrs Pherwani, you can whack me
as much as you want.

1283
01:16:54,880 --> 01:16:56,671
But please spare my life.

1284
01:16:56,755 --> 01:16:58,046
Fifty lakhs.

1285
01:16:58,130 --> 01:16:59,755
- [stammers]
- Fifty lakhs, Ramu.

1286
01:16:59,838 --> 01:17:01,046
Did you just say 50 lakhs?

1287
01:17:02,880 --> 01:17:04,880
Where am I gonna get 50 lakhs from?

1288
01:17:04,963 --> 01:17:07,713
Even if I sell both my kidneys,
I won't get 50 lakhs.

1289
01:17:07,796 --> 01:17:09,005
You know my circumstances.

1290
01:17:09,088 --> 01:17:10,713
I live in a rented apartment.

1291
01:17:11,963 --> 01:17:15,130
On top of that, you've made me
your slave, and pay me nothing.

1292
01:17:15,213 --> 01:17:17,796
I massage you, I dance for you,
wash your clothes, clean and mop,

1293
01:17:17,880 --> 01:17:20,088
I chase rats, kill lizards,
play a game of charades,

1294
01:17:20,171 --> 01:17:23,046
hide-and-seek, board games,
you made me catch a pigeon once.

1295
01:17:23,130 --> 01:17:25,505
I'm terrified of pigeons.
Why would you do that to me?

1296
01:17:26,171 --> 01:17:28,463
Honestly, I don't have that kind of money.

1297
01:17:28,546 --> 01:17:29,671
You don't have the money?

1298
01:17:29,755 --> 01:17:32,796
But last night when we went out
for dinner,

1299
01:17:32,880 --> 01:17:36,338
you were flashing your credit card,
and tipped the waiter so generously.

1300
01:17:37,546 --> 01:17:40,463
When did we go out? We didn't go anywhere.

1301
01:17:41,213 --> 01:17:44,088
I came over to your place, after which,
I went home, had some curry,

1302
01:17:44,171 --> 01:17:45,671
and went to bed.

1303
01:17:45,755 --> 01:17:47,463
You're making up stories in your head.

1304
01:17:48,171 --> 01:17:50,546
Look, Mrs Pherwani,
go see a doctor. Please.

1305
01:17:50,630 --> 01:17:52,130
Not a doctor.

1306
01:17:52,213 --> 01:17:54,338
I should let the police see your video.

1307
01:17:54,421 --> 01:17:56,630
Move your ass and arrange for that money.

1308
01:17:56,713 --> 01:17:58,880
Or I'll send your sorry ass to jail.

1309
01:17:58,963 --> 01:18:00,421
- [breathes heavily]
- But listen…

1310
01:18:00,505 --> 01:18:01,588
[beeping]

1311
01:18:02,796 --> 01:18:04,255
Hello, Fateha.

1312
01:18:05,213 --> 01:18:09,630
How can Pherwani miss your lovely party?

1313
01:18:09,713 --> 01:18:11,338
[chuckles] I'll be there.

1314
01:18:20,380 --> 01:18:21,380
Good job.

1315
01:18:27,463 --> 01:18:28,463
What's up, bro?

1316
01:18:29,130 --> 01:18:30,213
Not bargaining today?

1317
01:18:31,005 --> 01:18:33,088
- Did you win the lottery?
- [exhales]

1318
01:18:34,713 --> 01:18:36,421
Life has become worthless.

1319
01:18:37,421 --> 01:18:38,921
What bargaining can I ask for?

1320
01:18:41,796 --> 01:18:42,880
Ramakant.

1321
01:18:45,255 --> 01:18:46,338
What's going on, bro?

1322
01:18:48,338 --> 01:18:49,838
All okay?

1323
01:18:50,713 --> 01:18:51,755
[sighs]

1324
01:18:52,505 --> 01:18:54,005
I'm in deep shit, Guddu.

1325
01:18:55,588 --> 01:18:57,546
I'm caught in the clutches of some witch.

1326
01:19:13,921 --> 01:19:16,380
Honestly, I don't think
you're the kind of guy to have an affair.

1327
01:19:16,463 --> 01:19:17,838
It's not an affair.

1328
01:19:18,380 --> 01:19:19,755
It's blackmail.

1329
01:19:21,921 --> 01:19:23,005
Blackmail?

1330
01:19:23,630 --> 01:19:24,671
And Guddu,

1331
01:19:25,421 --> 01:19:27,255
you've got a bunch of connections
in Dubai, right?

1332
01:19:27,338 --> 01:19:28,796
Yeah.

1333
01:19:28,880 --> 01:19:32,213
Could that be any gangster-type
connections?

1334
01:19:39,755 --> 01:19:41,838
Eleven o'clock, tonight. Cheetah Bar.

1335
01:19:46,546 --> 01:19:47,963
[Pherwani] Ramu.

1336
01:19:48,046 --> 01:19:50,380
That witch. The witch.

1337
01:19:57,713 --> 01:20:00,338
I heard there's some witch
you wanna get rid of.

1338
01:20:03,213 --> 01:20:04,546
Guddu.

1339
01:20:04,630 --> 01:20:05,671
Come sit.

1340
01:20:06,380 --> 01:20:07,463
[dramatic music plays]

1341
01:20:11,671 --> 01:20:13,963
Where's that Dubai
connection we were gonna meet?

1342
01:20:18,755 --> 01:20:21,255
Day time, I'm Guddu AM.

1343
01:20:23,255 --> 01:20:26,255
Night time, I'm Guddu PM.

1344
01:20:26,338 --> 01:20:27,880
Pew!

1345
01:20:27,963 --> 01:20:29,546
So it's you?

1346
01:20:30,630 --> 01:20:31,838
Visiting card?

1347
01:20:31,921 --> 01:20:34,421
- Yeah.
- What if the police get hold of it?

1348
01:20:34,505 --> 01:20:39,671
And how will they? There's only one.
I show it and take it back.

1349
01:20:40,921 --> 01:20:42,213
So you'll fix it?

1350
01:20:42,296 --> 01:20:45,630
But have you ever
done something like this?

1351
01:20:45,713 --> 01:20:47,421
I'm making my debut for your sake.

1352
01:20:47,505 --> 01:20:49,046
Debut?

1353
01:20:49,838 --> 01:20:51,255
Guddu, it's not such a big deal.

1354
01:20:51,338 --> 01:20:53,255
You just have to get the video back
by threatening her.

1355
01:20:53,338 --> 01:20:54,880
It'll be done. Twenty-five grand only.

1356
01:20:54,963 --> 01:20:58,088
What? T-Twenty-five?

1357
01:20:58,755 --> 01:21:00,796
Guddu, but we are buddies, man.

1358
01:21:01,963 --> 01:21:04,338
Besides, I'm giving you a break.

1359
01:21:04,421 --> 01:21:07,088
Now, you tell me, does anyone stand
a chance these days without nepotism?

1360
01:21:07,171 --> 01:21:08,171
[sighs]

1361
01:21:08,255 --> 01:21:10,546
Dude, as a matter of fact,
you should be paying me.

1362
01:21:10,630 --> 01:21:11,880
Free.

1363
01:21:11,963 --> 01:21:13,046
Free.

1364
01:21:13,130 --> 01:21:14,755
- Free?
- Yeah. Free.

1365
01:21:15,505 --> 01:21:17,171
Deal. Eat. It's free.

1366
01:21:31,421 --> 01:21:32,921
Consider your job done.

1367
01:21:33,005 --> 01:21:34,005
Be careful.

1368
01:21:47,671 --> 01:21:48,963
[Pherwani] Ramu.

1369
01:21:54,338 --> 01:21:57,255
Hmm. [chuckles]

1370
01:22:00,838 --> 01:22:02,588
Oh, what is this?

1371
01:22:02,671 --> 01:22:05,255
What is this? What is this?

1372
01:22:05,338 --> 01:22:06,755
[inhales sharply]

1373
01:22:11,921 --> 01:22:14,838
Time to delete Ramakant's video, aunty.

1374
01:22:17,546 --> 01:22:18,671
[phone chimes]

1375
01:22:20,796 --> 01:22:21,921
[thunderclap]

1376
01:22:22,005 --> 01:22:25,380
WORK IS DONE.
COME TO THE OLD WOMAN'S HOUSE.

1377
01:22:35,046 --> 01:22:36,171
[Ramakant] Guddu.

1378
01:22:38,088 --> 01:22:39,213
Mrs Pherwani?

1379
01:22:40,671 --> 01:22:43,630
You threatened her so hard,
she passed out.

1380
01:22:43,713 --> 01:22:46,588
You have no idea
how deadly my friend here is.

1381
01:22:47,713 --> 01:22:50,755
Guddu, my brother, the video
has been deleted. Now we can party.

1382
01:22:51,546 --> 01:22:53,296
No, no, Guddu. Not on the rocks. No way.

1383
01:22:53,380 --> 01:22:55,755
Some ice. Can I get you some ice?
Ice? Sure.

1384
01:22:56,421 --> 01:22:57,630
Mrs Pherwani?

1385
01:22:58,338 --> 01:22:59,421
Is there some ice?

1386
01:23:00,046 --> 01:23:01,630
Okay, fine. You sleep. Carry on.

1387
01:23:03,421 --> 01:23:04,546
Guddu.

1388
01:23:04,630 --> 01:23:07,505
If only your father were alive today,
he'd be so proud of you.

1389
01:23:08,338 --> 01:23:09,671
[thunderclap]

1390
01:23:15,546 --> 01:23:16,880
Guddu, my buddy?

1391
01:23:24,755 --> 01:23:28,880
Guddu has joined his father in hell.
That good for nothing.

1392
01:23:30,588 --> 01:23:33,213
[breathing heavily]

1393
01:23:34,963 --> 01:23:36,838
What have you done to my friend, Guddu?

1394
01:23:41,338 --> 01:23:42,505
[gasps]

1395
01:23:43,130 --> 01:23:44,880
[groans]

1396
01:23:52,046 --> 01:23:55,088
[Ramakant crying]

1397
01:23:57,421 --> 01:23:59,130
Idiot.

1398
01:24:01,005 --> 01:24:03,421
Now you better dispose of the body.

1399
01:24:04,463 --> 01:24:07,921
Dispose of it? [stammers]
How do I do that?

1400
01:24:08,005 --> 01:24:10,213
I don't know how and where
these things are done.

1401
01:24:13,255 --> 01:24:15,630
I know the perfect place.

1402
01:24:29,005 --> 01:24:32,421
Wait. Wait. Not there.

1403
01:24:35,005 --> 01:24:36,088
There.

1404
01:24:37,088 --> 01:24:38,421
Why? Why not here?

1405
01:24:38,505 --> 01:24:40,046
Hmm.

1406
01:24:40,130 --> 01:24:42,630
The prince of this theme park
is buried there.

1407
01:24:44,005 --> 01:24:45,421
Mr Pherwani.

1408
01:24:45,505 --> 01:24:46,546
Huh?

1409
01:24:49,296 --> 01:24:52,213
He was so desperate to keep this stupid
place that he…

1410
01:24:52,880 --> 01:24:53,963
[scoffs]

1411
01:24:54,046 --> 01:24:55,380
Died?

1412
01:24:55,463 --> 01:24:56,671
[dogs howling in distance]

1413
01:24:58,588 --> 01:25:00,255
[thunderclap]

1414
01:25:09,588 --> 01:25:10,588
[groans]

1415
01:25:17,255 --> 01:25:18,296
[groans]

1416
01:25:41,338 --> 01:25:42,588
Huh?

1417
01:25:48,338 --> 01:25:49,421
What is this?

1418
01:25:50,130 --> 01:25:51,171
A pillow.

1419
01:25:52,088 --> 01:25:53,796
So your friend is nice and comfy.

1420
01:26:02,630 --> 01:26:04,255
I'm sorry, Guddu.

1421
01:26:10,630 --> 01:26:13,171
Do they lay you face up
or face down in your grave?

1422
01:26:14,588 --> 01:26:16,380
We cremate our dead, so I'm not sure.

1423
01:26:17,755 --> 01:26:20,963
- Face up.
- Face up.

1424
01:26:22,380 --> 01:26:23,380
Ramu!

1425
01:26:25,130 --> 01:26:26,338
[panting]

1426
01:26:27,755 --> 01:26:28,796
Huh?

1427
01:26:29,505 --> 01:26:32,338
One thing you better get into
your thick head, lover boy.

1428
01:26:33,213 --> 01:26:35,380
If anything happens to Malini,

1429
01:26:35,921 --> 01:26:40,338
that video of yours and this location pin
will go straight to the police.

1430
01:26:44,005 --> 01:26:47,088
- Come on, madam, I already told you…
- Madam.

1431
01:26:47,171 --> 01:26:49,213
First, you need to give it
to me in writing

1432
01:26:49,296 --> 01:26:51,838
that these poor orphan children
are not allowed to eat toast.

1433
01:26:51,921 --> 01:26:54,338
- Aren't we looking for your toaster?
- As if you're looking for it.

1434
01:26:54,421 --> 01:26:56,505
I gave you the thief's name,
address and everything.

1435
01:26:56,588 --> 01:26:58,963
But you people still can't find
my toaster for me?

1436
01:26:59,046 --> 01:27:00,463
One minute. One minute.

1437
01:27:01,713 --> 01:27:02,880
- Salunke.
- Yes, sir.

1438
01:27:04,046 --> 01:27:05,171
What kind of toaster?

1439
01:27:05,255 --> 01:27:08,713
Look, sir, it's my toaster. I even have
a picture on my phone to show you.

1440
01:27:15,880 --> 01:27:17,880
And where does he live,
this toaster thief?

1441
01:27:17,963 --> 01:27:22,171
Right there. In the Glen D'Souza's
apartment complex. In the next building.

1442
01:27:22,255 --> 01:27:23,921
Ramakant Parikh is his name.

1443
01:27:24,671 --> 01:27:25,963
He's Glen's tenant.

1444
01:27:26,046 --> 01:27:29,088
Actually, sir, we conducted
a thorough search of the apartment.

1445
01:27:29,171 --> 01:27:30,338
But no sign of the toaster.

1446
01:27:30,421 --> 01:27:33,546
Listen, sir, now I'll conduct a search and
show you how the toaster turns up.

1447
01:27:33,630 --> 01:27:35,171
No. Look, madam…

1448
01:27:35,255 --> 01:27:38,046
The police are doing their job.
If we find it, we'll let you know.

1449
01:27:38,130 --> 01:27:41,338
What will you people ever find?
Just give me my phone back.

1450
01:27:41,421 --> 01:27:44,380
- You just drink water and go to bed.
- Madam, I can live on fresh air as well.

1451
01:27:44,463 --> 01:27:45,880
Mmm. You're asking for a slap.

1452
01:27:52,046 --> 01:27:53,463
- [dramatic music plays]
- [scoffs]

1453
01:27:56,088 --> 01:27:58,546
SHREE SHARADASHRAM APARTMENTS
BORIVALI WEST, MUMBAI 400092

1454
01:27:59,380 --> 01:28:00,796
Where have you been all night?

1455
01:28:01,546 --> 01:28:03,463
Why was your phone switched off?

1456
01:28:04,546 --> 01:28:06,338
I-I went to the docks with Guddu.

1457
01:28:08,755 --> 01:28:11,296
So you were at the docks with Guddu, huh?

1458
01:28:12,046 --> 01:28:14,213
Or were you rolling around
in the mud with some pig?

1459
01:28:14,880 --> 01:28:16,963
It's too early
in the morning for all this.

1460
01:28:17,505 --> 01:28:20,671
You weren't here all night.
So I have to do this in the morning.

1461
01:28:20,755 --> 01:28:22,338
Now you too can pounce on me?

1462
01:28:22,421 --> 01:28:23,546
You too?

1463
01:28:24,880 --> 01:28:26,588
Who else is pouncing on you, tell me?

1464
01:28:28,296 --> 01:28:30,546
Shilpa, I need to pee. Let me go.

1465
01:28:30,630 --> 01:28:33,088
I really don't give a damn.
You can pee in your pants.

1466
01:28:33,171 --> 01:28:35,213
But I need to know,
where were you all night?

1467
01:28:35,296 --> 01:28:36,380
Tell me.

1468
01:28:36,463 --> 01:28:38,921
- [doorbell rings]
- Go get the door.

1469
01:28:39,005 --> 01:28:40,671
To hell with the door. Tell me now.

1470
01:28:40,755 --> 01:28:42,005
But I'm dying to pee.

1471
01:28:42,088 --> 01:28:44,796
I don't care. Pee in your pants
if you like. I said, tell me!

1472
01:28:45,713 --> 01:28:47,880
- [doorbell rings]
- Shilpa…

1473
01:28:54,796 --> 01:28:55,880
Ramakant?

1474
01:28:55,963 --> 01:28:57,588
Yes.

1475
01:28:57,671 --> 01:29:00,255
Mmm… Yeah, I got him. Let's go.

1476
01:29:00,338 --> 01:29:01,588
Shilpa!

1477
01:29:01,671 --> 01:29:03,713
- Hello, sir? Hold on, one second.
- [Balgaode] Keep walking!

1478
01:29:03,796 --> 01:29:06,005
What are you doing?
Where are you taking me?

1479
01:29:06,088 --> 01:29:08,671
- Just move. Move.
- Sir, just listen to me. Sir, look.

1480
01:29:08,755 --> 01:29:11,213
- Move. Move!
- Where are you… Shilpa! Shilpa!

1481
01:29:11,296 --> 01:29:13,296
Where are you…
I'll file a police complaint against you.

1482
01:29:13,380 --> 01:29:15,463
- You can't kidnap people like this.
- Yeah, go ahead and complain.

1483
01:29:15,546 --> 01:29:18,338
I am the police. And we're going
to the police station. Now move.

1484
01:29:18,421 --> 01:29:19,755
What? Sir… sir.

1485
01:29:19,838 --> 01:29:21,255
Ramakant!

1486
01:29:22,046 --> 01:29:23,046
- Sir… Shilpa!
- Stop!

1487
01:29:23,130 --> 01:29:24,796
- Sir, why are you harassing me, sir?
- Stop right there!

1488
01:29:24,880 --> 01:29:26,296
I'm harassing you? Huh?

1489
01:29:26,380 --> 01:29:28,421
You steal toasters from hungry orphans.

1490
01:29:29,296 --> 01:29:30,296
Toaster?

1491
01:29:31,005 --> 01:29:32,505
Okay, no.

1492
01:29:32,588 --> 01:29:35,421
You're looking for Glen's toaster, right?
What's hidden in that toaster?

1493
01:29:35,505 --> 01:29:37,255
Hey, shut up! What is she trying to say?

1494
01:29:37,338 --> 01:29:39,255
Stop playing detective. They're cops.
You'll get me in trouble.

1495
01:29:39,338 --> 01:29:42,296
Would you shut up? I overheard you talking
to someone on the phone.

1496
01:29:42,380 --> 01:29:43,671
What exactly is in that toaster?

1497
01:29:43,755 --> 01:29:45,255
Has she fallen on her head?

1498
01:29:45,338 --> 01:29:46,963
What he's asking is,
have you lost your mind?

1499
01:29:47,046 --> 01:29:49,505
- Shut up!
- That's him! That's the guy! That's him!

1500
01:29:49,588 --> 01:29:51,505
Hey! You bloody thief! Sir!

1501
01:29:51,588 --> 01:29:54,838
I'm telling you,
lay him on ice naked and then call me.

1502
01:29:54,921 --> 01:29:57,213
I'll thrash him so hard,
he'll never be able to have toast again.

1503
01:29:57,296 --> 01:30:00,463
Oh, God, woman. Why have you come here?
I'm handling the matter, can't you see?

1504
01:30:00,546 --> 01:30:04,463
Spare me, sir. The police have finally
woken up from their sleep.

1505
01:30:04,546 --> 01:30:05,713
I thought I'd handle it myself.

1506
01:30:05,796 --> 01:30:07,421
Why aren't you talking?
Tell them the truth.

1507
01:30:07,505 --> 01:30:08,630
- I definitely saw this guy.
- Hmm.

1508
01:30:08,713 --> 01:30:12,005
Inspector, I even put a sticker
on the toaster with my name on it.

1509
01:30:12,088 --> 01:30:15,171
This madam gave me
a good thrashing with her slipper.

1510
01:30:15,255 --> 01:30:17,838
She said, "Is this your father's toaster?"

1511
01:30:17,921 --> 01:30:20,380
Don't say anything more
than you're supposed to say.

1512
01:30:20,463 --> 01:30:22,255
Don't drag fathers into it. Understood?

1513
01:30:22,338 --> 01:30:24,338
So your name is Pichkoo?

1514
01:30:24,421 --> 01:30:27,713
- Yes, ma'am, how do you know?
- Because you're very famous, that's why.

1515
01:30:29,130 --> 01:30:30,546
You're involved in this too?

1516
01:30:31,713 --> 01:30:36,213
Involved? What… what involved?
Involved in what?

1517
01:30:36,296 --> 01:30:38,088
Look, sir.

1518
01:30:38,171 --> 01:30:41,130
Shilpa. One second.
One second. One second.

1519
01:30:41,213 --> 01:30:43,130
Was it me? It was me, right?

1520
01:30:44,338 --> 01:30:45,921
Turn… Turn around. Turn around.

1521
01:30:46,005 --> 01:30:47,255
Yes. Now tell me.

1522
01:30:47,880 --> 01:30:50,255
- Out of the three of us, who was the man?
- Hey!

1523
01:30:52,130 --> 01:30:54,546
- Hey!
- You see that, sir?

1524
01:30:54,630 --> 01:30:59,005
Sir! The price of that toaster was
5,000. I even double-checked online.

1525
01:30:59,088 --> 01:31:01,213
And what if we give you 5,000?

1526
01:31:01,296 --> 01:31:03,755
Will you take back your complaint?

1527
01:31:03,838 --> 01:31:05,755
Five thousand bucks? Yes, I will do it.

1528
01:31:05,838 --> 01:31:07,671
I'll buy it on online sale.

1529
01:31:08,755 --> 01:31:10,630
Here you go, 5,000.

1530
01:31:10,713 --> 01:31:12,421
No need to count. I'm sure it's fine.

1531
01:31:12,505 --> 01:31:15,421
Hmm. So now is the case closed?

1532
01:31:15,505 --> 01:31:17,505
Yes. The case is closed. Let him go.

1533
01:31:17,588 --> 01:31:19,963
What do you mean, "Let him go"?
How can we close the case just like that?

1534
01:31:20,046 --> 01:31:22,213
It's an out-of-court settlement, sir.
I got what I wanted.

1535
01:31:22,296 --> 01:31:24,046
- [stammers]
- Come with me. I'll deal with you.

1536
01:31:24,130 --> 01:31:26,505
You called me a man, right?
Let me show you. Let's go.

1537
01:31:29,088 --> 01:31:30,755
There are murders in this city.

1538
01:31:30,838 --> 01:31:32,630
There's blackmail in this city.

1539
01:31:33,380 --> 01:31:36,880
And here you are defaming a decent man
over a simple toaster?

1540
01:31:36,963 --> 01:31:39,880
He's a thief! He's not decent.

1541
01:31:39,963 --> 01:31:43,380
No, no, no. I know him very well.

1542
01:31:44,171 --> 01:31:45,421
Personally.

1543
01:31:45,505 --> 01:31:48,671
Isn't it? Now you may go.

1544
01:31:48,755 --> 01:31:53,130
Or should we file a complaint
against you too, for harassment?

1545
01:31:53,213 --> 01:31:54,713
Uh.

1546
01:31:55,296 --> 01:31:56,296
Hmm.

1547
01:31:57,213 --> 01:31:59,255
- Sir.
- Mmm.

1548
01:32:03,380 --> 01:32:04,963
Thank you, Mrs Pherwani.

1549
01:32:05,046 --> 01:32:06,213
We will pay you back.

1550
01:32:06,296 --> 01:32:08,713
Oh, no, no.
Don't even talk about it, please.

1551
01:32:08,796 --> 01:32:10,963
You two are like my own.

1552
01:32:11,046 --> 01:32:12,130
[chuckles]

1553
01:32:12,213 --> 01:32:16,296
Then I also have some right
over Ramakant, don't I?

1554
01:32:16,380 --> 01:32:17,755
Isn't it, Ramakant?

1555
01:32:18,421 --> 01:32:20,005
Hmm. Let's go.

1556
01:32:20,088 --> 01:32:21,713
Thank you.

1557
01:32:21,796 --> 01:32:24,005
- Welcome.
- Did you steal that toaster?

1558
01:32:24,088 --> 01:32:26,296
- No, Shilpa.
- Did you steal that toaster or not?

1559
01:32:26,380 --> 01:32:28,088
Listen.
Let me just thank her and come back.

1560
01:32:28,171 --> 01:32:31,505
- You've lied to me about everything.
- I'll tell you. Let me go and thank her.

1561
01:32:31,588 --> 01:32:33,005
Did you steal that toaster or not?
Tell me.

1562
01:32:33,088 --> 01:32:34,588
I'll tell you everything. One second.

1563
01:32:34,671 --> 01:32:36,463
You've lied to me about everything.
Everything!

1564
01:32:36,546 --> 01:32:39,171
No, Shilpa.
Lemme, lemme just go and thank her first.

1565
01:32:39,255 --> 01:32:40,796
Yeah, go. Go and say thank you. Go!

1566
01:32:40,880 --> 01:32:41,963
[grunts] Shilpa!

1567
01:32:44,005 --> 01:32:45,088
Shilp…

1568
01:32:46,213 --> 01:32:47,338
I… I'll be back.

1569
01:32:51,421 --> 01:32:53,838
Mrs Pherwani. Mrs Pherwani.

1570
01:32:54,505 --> 01:32:56,671
Are you trying to trap me?
Why'd you give that money to her?

1571
01:32:56,755 --> 01:32:58,296
I was handling it, right?

1572
01:33:00,338 --> 01:33:02,505
"In this dry, barren land,

1573
01:33:03,505 --> 01:33:05,171
a new bud has bloomed."

1574
01:33:05,255 --> 01:33:06,713
What?

1575
01:33:06,796 --> 01:33:11,588
"It's like a whole new life
is awakening," Ramu.

1576
01:33:11,671 --> 01:33:13,213
What shit are you reading, Mrs Pherwani?

1577
01:33:13,296 --> 01:33:14,755
What's with this life-awakening crap?

1578
01:33:19,130 --> 01:33:23,213
I'm going to be the mother of your child.

1579
01:33:23,296 --> 01:33:25,296
[gasps]

1580
01:33:29,421 --> 01:33:33,713
You're joking, right? Mrs Pherwani,
who gets pregnant just from a massage?

1581
01:33:33,796 --> 01:33:34,880
[temple bell ringing]

1582
01:33:43,213 --> 01:33:45,380
SHIV SHANKAR GANESH

1583
01:33:45,463 --> 01:33:47,088
Oh, dear Lord.

1584
01:33:47,171 --> 01:33:48,880
[bell chiming]

1585
01:33:51,880 --> 01:33:52,921
[sighs]

1586
01:33:54,463 --> 01:33:55,505
Oh, dear Lord.

1587
01:33:56,463 --> 01:33:58,171
You're the one who knows it all.

1588
01:33:58,255 --> 01:34:01,671
And today, you'll have to answer me.
Look. Please, please tell me.

1589
01:34:02,380 --> 01:34:05,338
Did, did I choose
the stinginess for myself?

1590
01:34:05,421 --> 01:34:06,796
I only inherited it!

1591
01:34:08,005 --> 01:34:10,213
My father was even a bigger miser than me.

1592
01:34:10,921 --> 01:34:15,005
Even with condoms, he was stingy.
Which is why I was born before my time.

1593
01:34:15,088 --> 01:34:16,796
[sighs]

1594
01:34:16,880 --> 01:34:19,671
And Lord, that crazy woman.

1595
01:34:19,755 --> 01:34:22,046
She keeps cooking up fake stories
on her own.

1596
01:34:22,130 --> 01:34:25,713
Have mercy on me. Please protect me, God.

1597
01:34:25,796 --> 01:34:27,046
[sighs]

1598
01:34:27,130 --> 01:34:28,880
Else my marriage will fall apart.

1599
01:34:29,463 --> 01:34:31,713
Shilpa will dump me and go away,
I swear, God.

1600
01:34:32,838 --> 01:34:35,296
And I won't be able to live without her.
You know that.

1601
01:34:36,213 --> 01:34:37,421
Now you decide.

1602
01:34:37,505 --> 01:34:39,588
Please. Please.

1603
01:34:43,838 --> 01:34:44,880
Got you!

1604
01:34:47,130 --> 01:34:49,546
Tell me. Where's that toaster?

1605
01:34:51,213 --> 01:34:53,296
[dramatic music plays]

1606
01:34:53,380 --> 01:34:55,255
[no audible dialogue]

1607
01:35:04,755 --> 01:35:05,755
AMRE SIR

1608
01:35:05,838 --> 01:35:08,796
WE FOUND THE TOASTER, SIR.
I'M SENDING THE LOCATION PIN.

1609
01:35:19,338 --> 01:35:20,588
Let's go.

1610
01:35:21,296 --> 01:35:22,380
Hey, move it.

1611
01:35:22,463 --> 01:35:25,963
No. You go, sir.
I don't wanna go. I'm scared.

1612
01:35:27,838 --> 01:35:30,380
Scared of an old hag? Come on. Be a man.

1613
01:35:30,463 --> 01:35:33,046
Listen, sir, this isn't a house.
It's a witch's cave.

1614
01:35:33,130 --> 01:35:35,421
- You don't know that lady.
- Hey, enough. Please.

1615
01:35:35,505 --> 01:35:38,130
Now do one thing. Send her a message.

1616
01:35:38,213 --> 01:35:40,296
Say you're coming. She'll open the door.

1617
01:35:41,213 --> 01:35:42,505
The door will be open.

1618
01:35:43,796 --> 01:35:45,046
Which apartment?

1619
01:35:45,671 --> 01:35:47,255
B Wing, 206.

1620
01:35:49,338 --> 01:35:50,921
All the best, sir.

1621
01:35:53,296 --> 01:35:54,546
Ding-dong!

1622
01:35:58,213 --> 01:35:59,505
Mrs Pherwani?

1623
01:36:04,088 --> 01:36:05,088
Ding-dong?

1624
01:36:05,671 --> 01:36:07,046
Ding-dong, ding-dong?

1625
01:36:08,338 --> 01:36:09,505
Bloody hell.

1626
01:36:10,796 --> 01:36:15,088
Where are you hiding with
the door wide open, Mrs Pherwani, huh?

1627
01:36:16,588 --> 01:36:19,421
A thief might break in and steal your
precious toaster.

1628
01:36:19,505 --> 01:36:20,755
Then you'll come complaining to me.

1629
01:36:20,838 --> 01:36:23,546
Come out, come out, wherever you are.

1630
01:36:23,630 --> 01:36:27,671
Turns out you're a bigger player than me.
Come on.

1631
01:36:27,755 --> 01:36:29,130
[phone chimes]

1632
01:36:32,713 --> 01:36:37,296
THE JOB IS DONE
COME TO THE OLD WOMAN'S HOUSE.

1633
01:36:41,088 --> 01:36:42,213
Mr Balgaode?

1634
01:36:43,755 --> 01:36:45,296
What!

1635
01:36:48,046 --> 01:36:49,338
Sir?

1636
01:36:49,421 --> 01:36:50,963
Hey! Sir!

1637
01:36:51,046 --> 01:36:53,796
Seems like you're hell-bent on making
Malini a serial killer?

1638
01:36:56,588 --> 01:36:58,713
You know what you need to do next.

1639
01:37:38,755 --> 01:37:41,171
Stingy even with this.

1640
01:37:41,255 --> 01:37:45,005
You buried your friend here.
You'll bury this guy here as well?

1641
01:37:46,046 --> 01:37:48,505
Am I a gravedigger, or what, huh?

1642
01:37:49,130 --> 01:37:50,671
Digging new graves every day?

1643
01:37:52,130 --> 01:37:54,421
Why don't you do it?
Come on. Here, take this.

1644
01:37:54,505 --> 01:37:55,796
[Shilpa] Ramakant!

1645
01:37:58,713 --> 01:38:00,463
W-What is this you're doing?

1646
01:38:00,546 --> 01:38:02,421
[gasps]

1647
01:38:02,505 --> 01:38:04,005
[laughs]

1648
01:38:07,838 --> 01:38:09,255
Game over, Ramakant.

1649
01:38:09,963 --> 01:38:12,713
Now that the grave is already dug…

1650
01:38:12,796 --> 01:38:17,088
…the secret buried between Ramakant
and Malini should also come out. Right?

1651
01:38:17,171 --> 01:38:19,505
What secret is she talking about,
Ramakant?

1652
01:38:19,588 --> 01:38:22,546
You know those cheap horror shows on TV

1653
01:38:22,630 --> 01:38:25,546
that she keeps watching?
Nothing's serious. It's a joke.

1654
01:38:25,630 --> 01:38:26,630
Now,

1655
01:38:28,005 --> 01:38:32,130
will Ramakant admit it or should Malini?

1656
01:38:32,213 --> 01:38:34,546
No, no, no! [stammering] Two minutes.

1657
01:38:34,630 --> 01:38:36,046
For two minutes, just stay quiet, please.

1658
01:38:36,130 --> 01:38:37,880
- I am…
- What will you say?

1659
01:38:37,963 --> 01:38:40,880
Ramakant is speaking.
You stay quiet. Be quiet.

1660
01:38:41,838 --> 01:38:42,963
Step back, please.

1661
01:38:43,046 --> 01:38:45,255
[stutters] Shilpa…

1662
01:38:45,838 --> 01:38:48,005
This old hag is out of her mind.

1663
01:38:48,088 --> 01:38:50,713
Try and understand what I'm saying, okay?

1664
01:38:50,796 --> 01:38:52,130
What is it?

1665
01:38:52,213 --> 01:38:54,171
Why are you scared of Ramakant?
What is it?

1666
01:38:54,255 --> 01:38:55,255
It's not Ramakant.

1667
01:38:56,255 --> 01:38:57,421
Someone more terrifying.

1668
01:38:58,546 --> 01:39:00,255
[neck cracks]

1669
01:39:02,505 --> 01:39:04,130
Have you heard of The Undertaker?

1670
01:39:04,213 --> 01:39:05,838
Yeah… that…

1671
01:39:05,921 --> 01:39:07,213
That's who I am.

1672
01:39:08,755 --> 01:39:12,588
You bloody old hag, you…

1673
01:39:12,671 --> 01:39:14,921
You think you can kill me?
You think you can kill me?

1674
01:39:15,005 --> 01:39:16,130
- [gags]
- I will.

1675
01:39:16,213 --> 01:39:17,338
[both scream]

1676
01:39:17,421 --> 01:39:19,588
I'll choke-slam you, yeah?

1677
01:39:19,671 --> 01:39:20,963
[grunts]

1678
01:39:21,046 --> 01:39:22,505
[breathes heavily]

1679
01:39:22,588 --> 01:39:25,255
Speak up! Where is the toaster? Tell me!

1680
01:39:25,338 --> 01:39:27,046
Why do you need the toaster?

1681
01:39:27,130 --> 01:39:28,130
Video.

1682
01:39:29,505 --> 01:39:32,380
It's inside the toaster, right?

1683
01:39:33,588 --> 01:39:35,796
I told you there's something
inside that toaster.

1684
01:39:35,880 --> 01:39:38,088
Shh. There's nothing.

1685
01:39:38,171 --> 01:39:40,588
How do you know
there's a video in the toaster?

1686
01:39:40,671 --> 01:39:44,130
Because I know everything.
Come on, hand it over now.

1687
01:39:46,963 --> 01:39:50,296
You can kill me, but I will
not tell you where the toaster is.

1688
01:39:50,380 --> 01:39:53,546
I will kill you. I'll kill you right here.

1689
01:39:53,630 --> 01:39:54,838
Get it, bitch?

1690
01:39:54,921 --> 01:39:57,338
Where is it? Where is the toaster?

1691
01:39:57,421 --> 01:39:58,880
[screams]

1692
01:40:00,255 --> 01:40:01,963
Ramakant's video is in the toaster.

1693
01:40:02,046 --> 01:40:05,588
Ramakant's video is in the toaster.
My video is in the toaster, Shilpa.

1694
01:40:05,671 --> 01:40:08,963
What are you blabbering about?
What video of Ramakant is in the toaster?

1695
01:40:09,046 --> 01:40:11,421
Hey, you moron!
What is this video of you now?

1696
01:40:11,505 --> 01:40:12,671
Huh?

1697
01:40:12,755 --> 01:40:18,713
I mean… Amre said there's a video of him
with some woman. You're saying it's your…

1698
01:40:18,796 --> 01:40:21,671
Oh! Ouch! [laughs]

1699
01:40:21,755 --> 01:40:24,463
That means you and Amre have something
going on. An affair?

1700
01:40:24,546 --> 01:40:25,630
Hey!

1701
01:40:25,713 --> 01:40:27,046
You guys are having an affair.

1702
01:40:27,130 --> 01:40:29,171
What the hell is he talking about?

1703
01:40:29,255 --> 01:40:31,838
Who is this Amre, and what
is going on between the two of you?

1704
01:40:31,921 --> 01:40:34,338
Listen. There's nothing!
Who's Amre? Who's Amre?

1705
01:40:34,421 --> 01:40:36,546
Your curse, my boss, Amre!

1706
01:40:36,630 --> 01:40:38,505
Hey, hey, hey! Hey!

1707
01:40:39,880 --> 01:40:42,755
Get it out! Get the toaster. Come on.

1708
01:40:42,838 --> 01:40:45,213
You'll hit me? You'll kill me?

1709
01:40:45,296 --> 01:40:46,796
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

1710
01:40:46,880 --> 01:40:48,005
[groans]

1711
01:40:48,088 --> 01:40:49,255
You did it!

1712
01:40:49,838 --> 01:40:50,921
How can you hit an old woman?

1713
01:40:51,005 --> 01:40:52,755
- Hey!
- Sir! Sir!

1714
01:40:52,838 --> 01:40:55,505
I need to have
that bloody toaster right now!

1715
01:40:55,588 --> 01:40:56,963
Sir, sir, sir, sir!

1716
01:40:57,046 --> 01:40:58,546
- Don't shoot, sir.
- [Shilpa shudders]

1717
01:40:58,630 --> 01:41:02,380
Shilpa, are you okay? Are you okay?
Are you okay? Huh? Sir, sir, sir.

1718
01:41:03,171 --> 01:41:04,671
R-Ramakant will bring you the toaster.

1719
01:41:04,755 --> 01:41:07,130
- Okay.
- Ramakant is bringing you the toaster.

1720
01:41:07,213 --> 01:41:09,088
- Hold your fire.
- Mmm.

1721
01:41:09,171 --> 01:41:10,671
[Shilpa sobs]

1722
01:41:12,630 --> 01:41:14,963
[grunts] Sir. Here's the toaster.

1723
01:41:15,046 --> 01:41:16,088
Yes!

1724
01:41:16,171 --> 01:41:17,463
- I'll get it out.
- Hmm.

1725
01:41:18,088 --> 01:41:19,255
[strains]

1726
01:41:25,796 --> 01:41:27,421
BAADU
LOCATION PIN

1727
01:41:30,755 --> 01:41:31,755
Thank you.

1728
01:41:42,213 --> 01:41:44,796
Check her out. Are you crazy or what?

1729
01:41:44,880 --> 01:41:47,005
- [gunshot]
- Hey! Hey!

1730
01:41:47,088 --> 01:41:50,046
- Stand back. And don't you dare move.
- Okay.

1731
01:41:50,130 --> 01:41:52,796
And you! You tell me the whole truth.

1732
01:41:52,880 --> 01:41:55,088
You're not just a miser, you know.

1733
01:41:55,171 --> 01:41:57,463
- You're also a liar.
- Let's go home and talk about it.

1734
01:41:57,546 --> 01:41:59,671
- Shut up! Shut up! Shut up! Shut up!
- [gunshot]

1735
01:41:59,755 --> 01:42:00,880
[whimpers]

1736
01:42:00,963 --> 01:42:02,630
[crying]

1737
01:42:06,463 --> 01:42:08,838
I don't wanna play anymore.
No more games for me.

1738
01:42:08,921 --> 01:42:11,338
- Kill me. Kill me.
- [panting]

1739
01:42:11,421 --> 01:42:13,088
Kill Ramakant, for God's sake!

1740
01:42:13,171 --> 01:42:15,296
Why do you keep calling yourself
Ramakant all the time?

